commit_message:
Cleanup oauth tests

In a lot of places this code was using dict.get() where [] makes
more sense because the code then assumes that the field was
present and had a value. Using .get() just means that if the code
changes the error would be an unexpected TypeError on a different
line than where the problem actually was.

Also, building of simple url strings was simplified to remove the
dict so that they could be kept on a single line.

Change-Id: I98b5631e02fe1456f0f583c4ec55c9ac0f8c4c35

commit_message:
Correctly normalize consumer fields on update

The self._normalize_dict() function in ConsumerCrudV3 creates a
copy of the consumer passed in and doesn't modify it, so this
line of code didn't do anything. The code is changed to use the
result as the new consumer rather than discarding it.

Closes-Bug: #1276857
Change-Id: Iec7573001ad73f0dc9192a4e74b1c35adc2cda4c

commit_message:
Create publishdocs target for publishing

tox -e publishdocs will be called by the post jenkins jobs to prepare
everything for publishing - and then the content of publish-docs
gets copied.

Change-Id: I9cdaf75ab7c5ec6bcc7df293ed0fc181434a5c2e

commit_message:
Revert to previous status if volume busy on delete

Currently when deleting a volume and it is busy, the manager will set
the status to 'available', even if the volume was in an error state.
The solution here is to save the previous state in the volume's
admin_metadata, and set to that.

Change-Id: I8e983d6e8e51b0ac8c43f773168a823b239be85b
Closes-Bug: #1236165

commit_message:
Prevent E500 when delayed delete is enabled

If delayed delete is enabled the user token was not being propagated
properly to the registry in all cases. This resulted in an authentication
error when the API attempted to connect to the registry, which in turn
caused a 500 error from the API.

Fix for bug 1238604.

Change-Id: Ifafc1613db034508abfce7ba5e4df582e6056c10

commit_message:
Fix volume transfer tests with tenant isolation disabled

This commit fixes the volume transfer tests for when tenant isolation
is disabled. The volume transfer tests still had a reference to the old
auth style to get the tenant name if tenant isolation was disabled.
The recent auth_provider refactor didn't update this call so the test
would fail. This commit updates it to use the new credential dict to
get the tenant_name

Change-Id: Ie7fe39baf6f62fa6966631d7890891252602ed8d

commit_message:
refactor keystone.conf template specs

add tests for every tunable.  organize code layout to reflect actual
template layout (group tests, in order).  also 3x performance gain by
collapsing 50+ chef converges into one.  remove 'pending' tests in
other platforms since there are no platform-specific tunables.

Change-Id: If0173d6dac94c6e64dcd4382eea036e41dafce2b
Closes-Bug: #1182562

commit_message:
Add InnoDB declaration for image_locations table

When a MySQL has as default table a different engine
other than InnoDB, (e.g. ndbcluster)
glance-mananger db_sync is failing.

Closes-Bug: #1270870
Change-Id: I5460deec98aed1b103fd1b06b88963c30e2d91f6

commit_message:
Make live migration validation optional

This live migration validation can leave the system locked, this patch
can help resolve those issues. Take an example: if the VM instance was
created with force host option, then the VM instance will not be able
to be migrated when checking scheduler hints. Thus, an option
'validate_by_scheduler' was introudced in order to make this validation
optional.

Co-Author: Yassine Lamgarchal <yassine.lamgarchal@enovance.com>

DocImpact
'validate_by_scheduler' was introduced to make live migration validation
optinoal.

Change-Id: I9a0e887ed385fd1a5808e4fe541cd83ac8a87c37
Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration

commit_message:
Fix 'size' as the optional para on do_create()

'size' should be optional parameter while creating a volume, because we
can create a volume from a snapshot or a source-volume or an image.

Change-Id: I1fc0b7f1cca6457efc7ce2d80815a672d0c85ad0
Closes-Bug: #1264055

The scenario is the following:

 1. This patch is merged.
 2. "!@#$%^*" seems obvious clearly, and some Cinder developer tries to add the validation
    code which denies a parameter including "!@#$%^*".
 3. If the developer post the patch, Jenkins test fails because of the test 1.

If we are in this scenario situation, we should post Tempest patch also and review it.
In addition, it is a little hard that Cinder developer would/should post a patch to Tempest because of the different project he/she is familiar with.

That wastes human resource and time.

So I don't like to add a test which is not clearly based on the specification.'}, {'account_id': 8998, 'date': '2014-01-24 03:10:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Create metadata with special chars

User also contain special chars in their metadata key or value name
It is more safe to make sure Openstack can accept that in our api.

commit_message:
Updates template_validate call to validate parameter_groups.

When calling template_validate, the parameter_groups will now
be checked for valid parameter references and parameter integrity
across groups.

Change-Id: I0cbca0d443b68b8932a155a637a9aedc8eb0c2f9
Implements: blueprint parameter-grouping-ordering

commit_message:
Correct `find_migrate_repo` usage

The `find_migrate_repo` function was never used with an argument although the
function interface presupposes an optional argument named
`package`.

$ grep -r "find_migrate_repo" keystone

    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()

The wrong function usage makes the function redundant (only one
string is needed there, all others are never executed) and forces redundant
code lines in other modules.
Database migration functions must take an extension module object and handle
a migration repository path with `find_migrate_repo` function.

::db_sync: [version, [package]]
::db_version: [package]
::db_version_control: [version, [package]]

`find_migrate_repo` raises an error when the migrate repository path doesn't
exist. The error should be handled to prevent further unexpected behaviour.

Closes-Bug: #1273336
Change-Id: Id62a1859a7e72139d25dfe91d29805660b4b7394

commit_message:
Don't try to stop a stack on a dead engine

Check that an engine is still alive before trying to stop the stack
during a stack-delete.

Change-Id: I3ce87dcefd5c4b5c542c3dc0d288655433bf69c4
Closes-Bug: #1279010

[{'created': '2014-02-12 15:11:27.000000000', 'message': 'Use `six.text_type` instead of `str` in cliutils

Several clients support printing dict with unicode using method
`print_dict`.

Using `unicode()` does not satisfy the Python 3 compatibility, so
we need to use `six.text_type` to allow print dict with unicode and
to support both Python 2 and 3.

Related to bp make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: If87fba3a5a53d2d6a97bd6d2cae6779b7dc81eed
'}]
commit_message:
Use `six.text_type` instead of `str` in cliutils

Several clients support printing dict with unicode using method
`print_dict`.

Using `unicode()` does not satisfy the Python 3 compatibility, so
we need to use `six.text_type` to allow print dict with unicode and
to support both Python 2 and 3.

Related to bp make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: If87fba3a5a53d2d6a97bd6d2cae6779b7dc81eed

commit_message:
Don't use private last_request variable

This is exposed in more recent versions of httpretty via a public method
rather than accessing it from the class.

Change-Id: I86949d94ac9b647ef577ee7db0ec4d664d6bc60b

commit_message:
Adds test_show_XX_fields cases to show some fields

This patch modifies the _show method to make it accept field_list.
It adds the cases to show some fields for network/subnet/port.
A related url example is
/v2.0/networks/103d47a3-XXXX-018c095ab35d?fields=id&fields=name

Change-Id: If2b9edd67ad0c43679332ec28ca80940c0c67d9e

commit_message:
Messaging backend selection

There is another patch that removes rabbitmq-server from
boot-stack's element dependencies.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72516/

This patch should be deployed before 72516.

This patch selects rabbitmq-server as the default messaging
backend using the *EXTRA_ARGS environment variable.

Change-Id: I63008be05923f74bb0fba344b581a07449c76298

[{'created': '2014-02-14 01:03:06.000000000', 'message': "Use database connection for keystone

The keystone configuration used the 'connection' option in the
'sql' section of the keystone.conf file. This option is deprecated
in favor of 'connection' in the 'database' section.

The keystone setup code is changed to use the option in the new
section rather than the deprecated one.

Change-Id: I62fd2f50ded3b8848e9e5225e88c80ed8fed3bff
"}]
commit_message:
Use database connection for keystone

The keystone configuration used the 'connection' option in the
'sql' section of the keystone.conf file. This option is deprecated
in favor of 'connection' in the 'database' section.

The keystone setup code is changed to use the option in the new
section rather than the deprecated one.

Change-Id: I62fd2f50ded3b8848e9e5225e88c80ed8fed3bff

commit_message:
Remove locale overrides form tox template

Change Iad912181bc00827908887d45a448f559d5083194 removed them from
tox.ini, so we should remove them from tox-tmpl.ini, too, so that
they don't reappear when tox.ini gets regenerated by toxgen.

Change-Id: Ib3544a95cf1e17230fea9b5699a9b84adb09d973

commit_message:
Reduce test and optional requirements to global requirements

Currently SQLAlchemy 0.9 and pyMySQL are not available on OpenStack
PyPi mirror, which means we can't run tests with them at gating.

Related-bug: 1280008
Change-Id: I23a8b7ab31d7fb9f6ae7454c242a2ba854484cea

commit_message:
Remove pyMysql testing until further notice

Currently pyMysql does not exist in the pypi
openstack mirror, so that means we can't run the
tests for mysql using py3.3 until either it exists
there or mysqldb is made py3.3 compat.

Change-Id: I48f652787bc6ed8f54258734316beb7e00082768

commit_message:
Permit specifying ovs bridge mappings too.

Another minor change to get a fully automated ci-overcloud deployment.

It's a shame this is all environment variable based - we'll have to
circle back and make this much nicer!

Change-Id: I5715a0ad6931c05dc10093c9abd5ecdb908e8246

messages:
[{'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-16 16:48:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

+2 for the spec change, this idea makes total sense to me in terms of what the user will be seeing in the UI.

I'm not 100% sure about the implementation. I guess this doesn't actually do anything yet anyway (we need to rework/replace the validate_template API output to actually make use of this), but on paper we're also modifying the CFN template format, which is not what we want IMO.

I think we should add a label() method to parameters.ParamSchema that just returns the name, and override it in hot.HOTParamSchema to return the label if available (and fall back to the name otherwise).

Over time we want to move toward doing all access to the parameters schema (in fact, the entire template) programmatically like this rather than by accessing dictionary keys directly, to abstract the different possible template formats. So if we're adding stuff we should do it that way from the beginning."}, {'account_id': 7253, 'date': '2013-12-16 17:20:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

Hey Zane,

Adding the label() method is a better way to maintain the compatibility between cfn and hot in this case. I'll look into it. I have been testing using the validate call and the code does already return the label as is. When you mentioned that you are worried because it appears like we are modifying the CFN format, is that because these code changes are going directly into the Parameter Schema instead of the HOTParamSchema? I'm not sure that I see a way around that for future modifications to the parameter schema since HOTParamSchema inherits from ParamSchema. I'm still learning the codebase though, so pointers are much appreciated."}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2013-12-16 18:52:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

You're completely correct. The plan is to refactor this so that the two formats inherit from a common base class, rather than one from the other. See I833edd8fad316220f56d6727fe1e3409f8fda6ee for some thoughts on where this is heading."}, {'account_id': 7714, 'date': '2013-12-17 00:34:18.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 7761, 'date': '2013-12-17 02:02:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Adds Parameter Label to HOT spec and parameter schema

This change will add the ability to put a human readable label
in a HOT Template for each parameter. This label will be used
to provide a better form label in any user interface when
available.

Change-Id: I8d815d1cfceb71c1ea0a9907f2afeb06dc4fca09
Implements: blueprint add-parameter-label-to-template

I found this worked:

    $ export MAVEN_OPTS=”-Dhttp.proxyHost=<host> -Dhttp.proxyPort=<port>”

...then run "mvn clean generate-sources"

My setup not have the latest plugins.'}, {'account_id': 860, 'date': '2014-01-02 17:53:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Comparing the in-line vs the WADL versions, I note there is a slight missmatch in the "URI Parameters" sections -- the table has a parameter called "{tenant_id}", whereas the URI has "/v1/{account}...".

X-Account-Meta (in table) appears to be missing the "-*" character that the description mentions.

X-Remove-Account-Meta (in the table) should probably be also X-Remove-Account-Meta-*

The account HEAD and POST should not have ?limit, ?marker, etc. in the URI (in table). This would match their (correct) absence from the URI Parameters tables.

On the plus side, X-Newest simply becomes an entry in the URI Parameters table instead of having it's own section (hence less prominent).'}, {'account_id': 2448, 'date': '2014-01-02 23:17:29.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 2448, 'date': '2014-01-02 23:17:59.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 5494, 'date': '2014-01-02 23:18:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Update Object Storage API Reference

Point to WADL files that generate the API Reference
  page so that the method descriptions and request
  and response parameters are consistent between
  these two docs:
    http://api.openstack.org/api-ref-objectstorage.html
      (API Reference page for Object Storage)
    http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-object-storage/1.0/
      (API Reference (or spec) for Object Storage)

Add descriptions of ACLs, FormPOST, TempURLs,
  StaticWeb, Bulk Upload, Bulk Delete, the OPTIONS operation
  (though this is implicit in CORS support)

Validate all code examples

Remove duplication.

Co-Author: Donagh McCabe

Closes-Bug: #1187119
Closes-Bug: #1214139
Closes-Bug: #1074198
Partial-Bug: #1255770

commit_message:
alembic with initial migration and tests

All sqlalchemy migrations and code associated
with them was removed including tests

Added all necessery alembic code to expose alembic specific features:
like revision and stamp

Added initial migration for alembic, that is fully in sync with models
including: uniques, indexes and columns params

Refactored test_versions to use alembic as migration api

Refactored BaseTestCase and Database fixture to use alembic as migration api

Change-Id: I8a91704d21ccea1b8135b9d724df5856ac21108c

commit_message:
Don't skip tests for some bugs

Skipping tests for a bug is a bad idea since if the bug is fixed
it's a manual process to find the affected test rather than being
found automatically by the tests.

Change-Id: I8109459bc825c5dc042e386432cb3496871f9862

commit_message:
Revert "Set sensible default for keystone's paste"

This reverts commit 7848b9d040ec59062389f2b32f88b342937cb612

The default config file shouldn't reference non-existing, unneeded files.

Closes-Bug: #1280692
Change-ID: Iad5bd8a079d5b57518335e5d8b66a54e47e19626

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-30 12:41:26.000000000', 'message': "Further preparation for transition to guest agent

 * Added abstract classes defining remote interface. The first class
   is for driver and the second one is for remote object. Note:
   execute_on_vm_interactive is not included into the later interface
   as it is not used in anywhere.
 * Now driver can provide additional part for userdata. This will be
   used by agent driver to setup guest agent on instances.
 * SSH opts are moved from ssh_remote.py to remote.py. While
   ssh_remote.py is the best place for them, together with change #1
   opts created circular imports:
     * remote.py imports ssh_remote.py to get options
     * ssh_remote.py imports remote.py to get abstract classes
   The problem can be resolved by moving abstract classes to a new
   module, say remote_common.py. But I prefer the variant I've
   implemented.
 * Fixed tests to work with the changes.

Change-Id: I2ccae4df7b664c612fd15a3e9578af5b7dd6f81c

commit_message:
Further preparation for transition to guest agent

 * Added abstract classes defining remote interface. The first class
   is for driver and the second one is for remote object. Note:
   execute_on_vm_interactive is not included into the later interface
   as it is not used in anywhere.
 * Now driver can provide additional part for userdata. This will be
   used by agent driver to setup guest agent on instances.
 * SSH opts are moved from ssh_remote.py to remote.py. While
   ssh_remote.py is the best place for them, together with change #1
   opts created circular imports:
     * remote.py imports ssh_remote.py to get options
     * ssh_remote.py imports remote.py to get abstract classes
   The problem can be resolved by moving abstract classes to a new
   module, say remote_common.py. But I prefer the variant I've
   implemented.
 * Fixed tests to work with the changes.

Implements: blueprint guest-agent
Change-Id: I2ccae4df7b664c612fd15a3e9578af5b7dd6f81c

commit_message:
Correct PXEPrivateMethodsTestCase.setUp

Unit tests within the PXEPrivateMethodsTestCase test class have been
sporadically failing on py26 test nodes since f14dacb7. That commit
introduced tests that interacted with the DB without inheriting from
DbTestCase, and loaded a driver via stevedore without mocking the
extension manager loading.

This patch corrects the above ommissions.

Change-Id: I2f930db7d3bb8abe120ce24a604f800c2e861fca
Closes-bug: #1279992

commit_message:
Make live LDAP user DN match the default from devstack

The default LDAP user DN in devstack uses the "cn" attribute in
the RDN.  The live LDAP test default configuration is supposed to
match the default devstack config, but the RDN is incorrectly
using the "dc" attribute.  This patch corrects the live LDAP
default config to match devstack.

Change-Id: Iee49606526047105b4e60142af32b4ec81a19444
Closes-Bug: 1280509

devel-1 (Havana now) is current stable release, where most of the backports are done.

commit_message:
Locally override bad keystone default.

I935c5144728d04c59abaee9a515e249ef0d24477 in keystone added a default
that references a non-existing (and not needed paste.ini file).

We'll back this out when the bug in keystone is closed.

Closes-Bug: #1280692
Change-Id: I04c5c2f9863a5e16b2b51eef37042194e23d8f43

REST API for software config

This REST API creates one new base path to manage config entities:

* /{tenant_id}/software_configs

Implements: blueprint hot-software-config-rest

Avishay,

Spent a little time looking at why this was failing UT and was able to recreate it.  It appears that either this part of the test case is not valid:  

            # Check bad output from lsfabric for the 2nd volume
            if protocol == 'FC' and self.USESIM:
                for error in ['remove_field', 'header_mismatch']:
                    self.sim.error_injection('lsfabric', error)
                    self.assertRaises(exception.VolumeBackendAPIException,
                                      self.driver.initialize_connection,
                                      volume2, self._connector)

Or that the code was not written to do what is expected and it was previously hitting an exception due to the bug you fixed.

Looking at the code it appears that this would jsut cause the first part of get_host_from_connector to fail and that it would then move on to the exhaustive approach where it recovers?

I was going to maybe push up a change to remove that part of the test but wanted your feedback first."}, {'account_id': 4355, 'date': '2014-02-15 17:27:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned'}, {'account_id': 4355, 'date': '2014-02-16 08:54:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Jay, the failure was due to initialize_connection being in iSCSI mode.  See the update to Zoltan's patch."}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2014-02-13 13:03:40.000000000', 'message': 'Storwize/SVC: Add delim to lsfabric

The lsfabric command in the Storwize/SVC omitted the delimeter and so
the output was not correctly parsed by the driver. This patch simply
adds it. Also make sure we are comparing lower-case WWPNs to ensure
host lookup success.

Change-Id: I50360401c4b12c8c38b7b433be660a65dd2fbda5
Closes-bug: 1279758
'}]
commit_message:
Storwize/SVC: Add delim to lsfabric

The lsfabric command in the Storwize/SVC omitted the delimeter and so
the output was not correctly parsed by the driver. This patch simply
adds it. Also make sure we are comparing lower-case WWPNs to ensure
host lookup success.

Change-Id: I50360401c4b12c8c38b7b433be660a65dd2fbda5
Closes-bug: 1279758

Update delete method for heat flow

Reasons:
- saved stack id gave to trove an
ability to perform actions over stacks;

Changes:
- updating BuildInstanceTask._delete_resource;

commit_message:
Skip curl pip package, if exists

It can save several seconds for dodgy network.
If the existing pip package is not in the good state,
the later tar operation will fail. Thus no need to worry
for using a wrong pip package

recheck bug 1253896'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2013-12-13 19:59:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I'm not sure about associating this to the bug that's referenced.  Particularly without updating the bug first and changing the project it's logged against etc. also I'm wondering, while adding a log message is probably ok, maybe we should look at adding some explicit info to docs (if it's not there already).

What would be really cool is to send an update back to Cinder to indicate what device the volume got attached as after everything's finally done.  This would also allow us to just use /dev/auto all the time anyway and avoid all of this confusion.  In other words, I don't remember exactly why returning the device_name from the utils call isn't working, but maybe it would be better to just skip all of that completely.

We'd as for volume-attach and could omit or ignore the device altogether for those that support it, and after the attach is complete have the nova api send an update to Cinder to let it know what the dev file ended up being?

It appears that adding anything to the API is quite the ordeal but I think that's what should happen here."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-13 21:02:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Works for me

commit_message:
Added msg info in nova CLI when attaching volume

Added warning log message in nova CLI, in order to inform that device name may
not match the proposed one.
The intention is to provide more information when device names don't match due
to hypervisor limitations or naming convention.

Change-Id: I2dea3d3fb6f80345c8e4c968a5295c6c09aa3065
Partial-Bug: #1217874

commit_message:
Fix AttributeErrors when the nova v3_api is disabled

The setUpClass when the v3 api is not enabled, tries to call
the tearDownClass-es, before the client helper variables are set.

Change-Id: I2f289d36bec21da72c7713e6a91c449d350e9a7b

commit_message:
some params for create flavor incorrectly checked

The flavor parameters name, ram, vcpus and disk for create flavor are
not checked correctly. When create flavor without name, it throws
exception with message:"name is not a string or unicode". I think it
should throw exception with message:"name must be specified for
flavor creation". The param ram, vcpus and disk have the same problem.
Because it didn't check whether the body contains the param.

Change-Id: I74feacd5e336d4a67948849769420c54a56bdae1
Closes-Bug: #1253525

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I16be1cbc7e902dfa85229ab2202be1bfd3479131

Infra has patches almost landed to create and upload wheels on every release"}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2013-11-21 18:40:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Do not merge

Just saw the note that these should not be merged.'}, {'account_id': 4375, 'date': '2013-11-22 11:20:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> This is incorrect. universal indicates that a created wheel works with both py2 and py3.

Well, currently we've got some missing pieces like eventlet here but IMO for the wheel to be published it's not really relevant if the code _really_ works with Py3k. The "universal" flag just adds

Tag: py2-none-any
Tag: py3-none-any

to the dist-info/WHEEl file. Without that, "python setup.py bdist_wheel" would just build a wheel with the ABI tag of the used interpreter, which results in e.g. "Tag: py27-none-any". However, that's not really true either since the code happily runs with py26. 

> We can build wheels without this.

Sure, but here "universal" is first and foremost a speed-up to avoid creating a venv for each ABI target (2.6, 2.7, 3,3, ...). With that, you wouldn't have to push several wheels, but just one. Furthermore, if you run "tox" with pip's cache setup, you would only have one download rather than several.

> Infra has patches almost landed to create and upload wheels on every release

Ok, didn't know that, can you point me to these?'}, {'account_id': 4375, 'date': '2013-11-22 12:23:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

In PEP-427, this is the first advantage over egg:

"Wheel is an installation format; egg is importable. Wheel archives do not need to include .pyc and are less tied to a specific Python version or implementation. commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: If7cce72f73e9522b3e7bcd1f1b94c58c476c0a2b

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: Iead561be2c524af8672884b3a87cc2af992d75ce

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I773f875f330e69b43c84638497e543be64f8e223

commit_message:
Test tempest decorators used on integration tests

The follow decorators are tested:
 * test.attr
 * test.stresstest
 * test.services
 * test.skip_because
 * test.requires_ext

Partially implements bp unit-tests

Change-Id: Idb9d99b085b396365e662aa2c7fcfa3751e7bf5a

six be used in general for python 3 compatibility.

commit_message:
Restructure Marconi plugin directory structure

Moving the queue resource under resources. This allows for the
separate doc generation between resources and other package modules

Change-Id: Icb402bde8e38114f4144252b93df0cb050d2e5f3

Nice patch.

We (Yves and me) also found another problem with the OVS agent [1]. Libvirt or Nova [1] removed an re-added quickly VM ports to the br-int during a reboot. But the OVS agent have not enough time to make a diff between two loop iterations, it did not realize the VM TAP interface was removed and added. But the LVID tag of this TAP disappears when it was removed and needs to be re-added by the OVS agent. I think we could correct that pb with your proposed patch. What do you think?

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1240849
[2] I think it's Nova which removes and re-adds the VM port into br-int because 'external-id' was re-populated. But it's need to be confirmed and perhaps it's also a Nova bug.

Nit: I know it's a WIP but RYU plugin also uses 'get_vif_port_set' method."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-10 08:48:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I only ran unit tests for the ryu plugin and they passed, but that was probably because they're heavily mocking out library calls.

As you can see this patch fails the gate, so there is something else to fix before I proceed to address the other problem.
If you want to do it in the meanwhile, you can either build on this patch or push another patch. If you want to avoid conflict issue I will keep this in WIP until yours merge."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-10 10:02:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I have looked back at my patch and concluded it's rubbish.
(For Americans, that would be trash)

1) the optimization is flawed since one would need to check whether the port still exist anyway. The device loop can take minutes and so it's normal the device goes away in the meanwhile. As I've been doing a bit of work to take the device loop time down, I should have known better.
2) the real optimization would be to avoid the plugin call if the port has gone on the integration bridge, and this should be done.
3) changing the interface of a library method without providing any backward compaitbility is something that alone would grant the -2 on any patch.
4) real optimization regarding fetching port changes from ovsdb should involve the ovs db monitor, which already collects this information.

I will therefore rework this patch to stick to fixing the ofport not specified issue, and perhaps doing the optimization pertaining not going to the plugin if the port disappears.

Summarizing - shame on you Salvatore, I am really disappointed with your work."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-13 22:52:12.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-13 22:53:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: No score

[{'created': '2014-01-10 01:49:17.000000000', 'message': "Optimize VIF retrieval and avoid regex parsing errors

The OVS agent port processing routine fetches ports twice.
In a first call it performs a 'list' operatiobretrieving name and
external ids, whereas in a second call it performs a 'find' operation
retrieving the ofport as well.
The two calls can be combined retrieving the ofport in the 'list'
operation. This adds little overhead to the first call and removes
the need for the second call.

Moreover, get_vif_port_set is also modified in order to not return
OVS ports for which the ofport is not yet assigned.
This patch therefore avoids an observed issue by which
get_vif_port_by_id fails to match a regex on the output of ovs-vsctl
as the ofport attribute is unspecified.

As get_vif_port_by_id is also used elsewhere in the agent, it has
been enhanced in order to tolerate situations in which ofport has not
yet been assigned

Change-Id: Icf7f0c7d6fe5239a358567cc9dc9db8ec11c15be
Partial-Bug: #1253896
"}, {'created': '2014-01-13 22:52:12.000000000', 'message': 'Avoid processing ports which are not yet ready

This patch changes get_vif_port_set in order to not return
OVS ports for which the ofport is not yet assigned, thus avoiding
a regex match failure in get_vif_port_by_id.
Because of this failure, treat_vif_port is unable to wire
the port.
As get_vif_port_by_id is also used elsewhere in the agent, it has
been enhanced in order to tolerate situations in which ofport might
have not yet been assigned.

Finally, this patch avoids fetching device details from the plugin
for ports which have disappeared from the OVS bridge. This is a
little optimization which might be beneficial for short lived ports.

commit_message:
Avoid processing ports which are not yet ready

This patch changes get_vif_port_set in order to not return
OVS ports for which the ofport is not yet assigned, thus avoiding
a regex match failure in get_vif_port_by_id.
Because of this failure, treat_vif_port is unable to wire
the port.
As get_vif_port_by_id is also used elsewhere in the agent, it has
been enhanced in order to tolerate situations in which ofport might
have not yet been assigned.

The ofport field is added to the list of those monitored by the
SimpleInterfaceMonitor. This will guarantee an event is generated
when the ofport is assigned to a port. Otherwise there is a risk
a port would be never processed if it was not yet ready the first
time is was detected. This change won't trigger any extra processing
on the agent side.

Finally, this patch avoids fetching device details from the plugin
for ports which have disappeared from the OVS bridge. This is a
little optimization which might be beneficial for short lived ports.

Change-Id: Icf7f0c7d6fe5239a358567cc9dc9db8ec11c15be
Partial-Bug: #1253896

commit_message:
Add .idea to .gitignore

    .idea folder is a specific PyCharm directory, adding it to .gitignore
    will avoid some mistakes.

Fixes bug #1253467

Change-Id: Ic9879b71783d9ea072a2b7d1b94558bfb20ec9ea

'}]
commit_message:
Set DEFAULT_IMAGE_NAME for Docker hypervisor

This allows the tempest configuration to set the right
image for booting docker containers with Nova.

Since glance uploads are not yet integrated in devstack,
IMAGE_URLS remains empty.

Change-Id: I5df153cd1d5e1411bb3c11816122ce280148e129

commit_message:
Added the import of lib/infra

This fixes an error in the devstack/functions
setup_develop call, which tries to cd to
$REQUIREMENTS_DIR, which is created in lib/infra

Change-Id: Ie65d2ba83547acc4ea36d1191e6e90dc21da1fa7
Closes-Bug: #1276365

commit_message:
Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using
the "--pre" option which is the default in tox. "--pre" means
"Include pre-release and development versions." By default, pip will
only install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior
we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>

commit_message:
Make floating_ips module use FixedIP object

This makes the network.floating_ips module use the FixedIP
objects instead of direct database interaction.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I09505d480bae0f764b1edf92722e1d2ed1652e61

commit_message:
Make floating_ips module use Network object

This makes the network.floating_ips module use the Network object
instead of going direct to the database.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I589881515fa43f9527a466f9eb22df2768ef3f3a

commit_message:
Make floating_ips module use Service object

This makes the network.floating_ips module use the Service object
for its query instead of direct database access.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I612b032824d828cf2104dd281bb88a4ecba6c8b6

commit_message:
Make floating_ips module use Instance object

This makes the network.floating_ips module use the Instance object
for queries instead of direct database access.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I213ff4476c3e8277f9df09941e24a1374a1aa569

commit_message:
Add searchDepth when getClusterInfo called.

Without searchDepth, getClusterInfo shows every volume and
snapshot. It's an unused information and takes very long time.

Change-Id: Id590e3023f4446f01b965baf4e8ac61980101067
Closes-Bug: 1276388

commit_message:
Fix up the overcloud ci job

We need to source undercloudrc to ensure were using the correct cloud.

devtest_overcloud doesn't take a data file as the first param passing
one in sets it to NeutronPublicInterface in the heat template.

Change-Id: Ie989050a30792d07662ce17520810ba01d43c242

HA undercloud wouldn't work with this approach anyway :)

commit_message:
Fix wrong example of "nova_endpoint_template"

In cinder.conf

e.g. http://localhost:8774/v2/%(tenant_id)s

should be

e.g. http://localhost:8774/v2/%(project_id)s

Change-Id: I7dd3be9bc9d2e8f26619b00b5bdbc66505a984b2
Closes-Bug: #1279747

commit_message:
Replace assertEqual(None, *) with assertIsNone in tests

Replace assertEqual(None, *) with assertIsNone in tests to have
more clear messages in case of failure.

commit_message:
Add EMC SMI-S FC Driver in Cinder

Add an EMC SMI-S FC Driver in Cinder. It supports all required
driver features.
Also made enhancements to the existing SMI-S iSCSI Driver
(performance enhancement, multiple pool support and thick/thin
provisioning, extend volume).
emc_smis_common.py is the common code used by both iSCSI driver
(emc_smis_iscsi.py) and FC driver (emc_smis_fc.py).

Implements blueprint emc-fibre-channel-volume-driver

Change-Id: Idace398ef60863811911511bcbbfcecb3bf58270

commit_message:
Remove dependent module py3kcompat

Module py3kcompat was removed from oslo-incubator, we can use
six directly.

Change-Id: I6c4266b71312ae53ecaedbd2ce1a865e60eb8d50
Closes-Bug: #1280033

commit_message:
fix templatetag for no fractional bytes

In django 1.6, testing 0.0005 MB fails due to rounding issues.

Since a fractional byte makes no sense, just casting the float
value to an int.

Partially-implements: blueprint django-1point6
Change-Id: Id82faf32f0670f6342dac87a08affc10c7fda8de

commit_message:
fix misspelling - "simple—a " and "acount"

*section_objectstorage-components.xml:
L164: "Implementing a partition is conceptually simplea partition is ..."
is actually want to say "Implementing a partition is conceptually simple,
a partition is ..."

L230: "acount" -> "account"

backport: none

Change-Id: I55ff60d62d953012eb827e37c7bb7885de024f2b
Closes-Bug: #1278753

Fix openSUSE dashboard file locations

Closes-Bug: #1279892

of the one in V3 controller.

LDAP: document enabled_emulation

 - Add documentation to the Configuration page for enabled_emulation
 - Fix a comment about the default value used for enabled_emulation

commit_message:
Rename _run_scenario_loop --> _run_scenario_once

This is to make it clear that the function does not run the whole loop
but only one iteration of it.

Change-Id: Idfed07af7842883eb4b6c58023acb3feaf941342
Trello: https://trello.com/c/crjvWNbX

commit_message:
Change Google Analytics counter

according to google's support page, this one-line change will make
"Google Analytics collects the information it normally does,
as well as the DoubleClick cookie when that cookie is present".

Change-Id: I9e2179329a85690bcbefb6efbd3901bff0dded9b
Closes-Bug: #1271485

commit_message:
Use WebOb directly in ec2_token middleware

When https://review.openstack.org/#/c/71494/ was introduced, it
forgot to change ec2_token as well. This caused errors when building
docs.

Change-Id: I051519c815ed5ae60ec07203073131db1e031e10

commit_message:
Add lockfile and kombu as requirements for keystone

Sphinx is failing to build because we do not list
lockfile or kombu in either requirements file.

Change-Id: Ic31870c283a18958cd61e51bc56ed771732ee753

The patch removes usage of StubOutClassWithMocks with keystone Client
class, which doesn't work anymore now that there is an ABC in the MRO.

Change-Id: I4e8ff2cde2723060faf9906ecf51b13911ac5f42
Closes-Bug: #1279907

commit_message:
Fix incompatibilities in tests with keystoneclient 0.6

The patch removes usage of StubOutClassWithMocks with keystone Client
class, which doesn't work anymore now that there is an ABC in the MRO.

Change-Id: I4e8ff2cde2723060faf9906ecf51b13911ac5f42
Closes-Bug: #1279907

commit_message:
Remove invalid parameter of quota-update

nova quota-update doesn't support update '--gigabytes' and '--volumes', but
CLI  include these two parameter, so it should remove these two parameter
from novaclient

Change-Id: I9db39dd397ba3368f214377f37b56ac4f4f3864c
Closes-bug: #1277673

commit_message:
Fix misspellings in openstack-manuals

Fix misspellings detected by:
* pip install misspellings
* git ls-files | grep -v locale | misspellings -f -

commit_message:
Count memory and disk slots once in cells state manager

If multiple instance types in a cell had the same memory_mb value or
root_gb + ephemeral_gb added to the same value, then capacity counts
would be inaccurate since slots would get counted multiple times.
Rather than counting based on instance type it is now based on the set
of memory or disk values pulled from instance types.

Change-Id: Iaded7fa69dadb4aa0335ef1569975bdfcb2767c6
Closes-bug: #1276728

commit_message:
Flavor show api will not show deleted flavors

* Do not show deleted flavors for flavor show api call
* Return deleted flavor details with v3 server show api call
* Not showing deleted flavors because flavor id are not unique
  for deleted/non-deleted flavors and this can return duplicates during
  "nova show"/ server show api call

Closes-Bug: #1153926
Change-Id: Ia38a6ad64f2c216b50c5a955a4f3f6d66f6424da

commit_message:
Use six.moves.urllib.parse instead of urlparse

To keep Python 3.x compatibility, use six.moves.urllib.parse to
replace urlparse.

Change-Id: I81333ca4d6ed88b2d491657170f526cbe9671d1f

commit_message:
Change 'update default quotas' success and failure messages

Success and failure messages include formatting that adds name,
which makes for awkward phrasing when displayed to the user.
Removed formatting to clarify message text for both success and
failure messages.

Change-Id: Id754ec9cb132ba82c07c13b05c76367739d3faaf
Closes-Bug: #1274654

subject: Make object upload success message translatable.

Hi ZhiWei, 

Thanks for the review. 

In order to reproduce the problem, I simply installed ceilometer with the metering cookbook and tried to use the ceilometer client. All client requests fail, and if you turn on debug mode you can see that the URLs are incorrect. I have documented the problem in a bug here: https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-chef/+bug/1277742

I agree that since this is an attribute it can be set by the user before the run, but I think out of the box the cookbook should work without having to specify an endpoint path, and that requires the default value to be correct.

If you notice, installing OpenStack by devstack does not create an endpoint with a /v1 path, it creates an endpoint with a / path, like what I am trying to do here. 

About the test cases that would fail in the metering cookbook, I have a patch out to update those here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72028/

Thanks again.'}, {'account_id': 9488, 'date': '2014-02-11 02:36:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

commit_message:
Fix metering service endpoint path

After installing ceilometer with the metering cookbook, invoking the
ceilometer CLI fails because the API base URL used is
http://127.0.0.1:8777/v1/v2 which means that the base endpoint path of
/v1 is incorrect and it should be simply /.

Change-Id: Id65a17a888175c7b2fe2d3171147cedb66921cc9
Partial-Bug: #1277742

commit_message:
Unneeded identity reg done for api-cfn

When the heat cloud formation (api-cfn recipe) is not needed and
not used, the identity recipe still creates service and endpoint
identity registrations for it. I added a check to see if the
api-cfn recipe is in the run_list, suggestions welcome for better
ways to approach this.

Change-Id: I5f326a66f005f0553aecd8cea798a224d76f57c4
Closes-bug: 1279577

commit_message:
Added recommendation for reserved_host_memory_mb value

The default for reserved_host_memory_mb is 512 MB but because the
vCenter driver reports memory available to the VMs, VMware suggests
setting this value to 0 MB. Added this recommendation to the
 VMwareVCDriver configuration options section

Change-Id: I11e01ff36a4d91c2c268b2ece65b4e7e19990468
Closes-Bug: #1267303

commit_message:
Create publishdocs target for publishing

tox -e publishdocs will be called by the post jenkins jobs to prepare
everything for publishing - and then the content of publish-docs
gets copied.

commit_message:
XenAPI: Report the CPU details correctly

Driver was not filling in the cpu_count in the correct field.
Also added VM vcpu count

Change-Id: I6339d7fd4faffcd5320fd86b55ff3a5e3515e2bf
Closes-bug: 1192528

commit_message:
fix ips to 'ips' in APIRouter

Actually ips in `ips in init_only` would not be valued as True because
ips is a moudle object not a string. Fixing this to string 'ips' could
prevent potential issues and improve readability.

Change-Id: I74564349e1fef00e7430cfb0547b3ad87c8e471c

Adding first_address attribute for port resource

This patch give availability for getting fixed ip address easily.

Closes-bug: #1262196

commit_message:
WIP: Enable H302 rule

DO NOT MERGE because this is 'work in progress'.

This commit is just enabling H302 rule. We may take a long time for
correcting all files . So this can check the status of the resolving
H302 violation.

commit_message:
Fix misspellings in openstack-doc-tools

Fix misspellings detected by:
* pip install misspellings
* git ls-files | grep -v locale | misspellings -f -

Change-Id: Ia6fa0ca03cd7c1d17f75cc349f9dba56e93f56b2
Closes-Bug: #1257295

commit_message:
Store scheduler_hints in instance_system_metadata when create instance

Store scheduler_hints in instance_system_metadata when create instance,
the scheduler_hints can be later used by live migration or evacuate for
host validation.

Co-Author: Yassine Lamgarchal <yassine.lamgarchal@enovance.com>

Change-Id: I6a919bdab6c5ca472b331b8ac76284925a5664f2
Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration

commit_message:
implements:bp/fsl-sdn-os-mech-driver::fsl mech driver

Freescale SDN Mechanism Driver to support CRD service

A new directory 'freescale' is created to hold the code in
ml2/drivers.

The following new files were added:

neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/freescale/README : README for driver
neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/freescale/__init__.py
neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/freescale/client.py : CRD helper class for use in driver.
neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/freescale/mech_fslsdn.py: FSl SDN ML2 Driver

The following files are modified:

neutron/tests/unit/ml2/drivers/test_fslsdn_mech.py: updated 'import' path with new file path

Change-Id: I091d51b68f5d07e64e553638b3bb070462dd077b

commit_message:
Support peer discovery through the metadata service

Adds an endpoint to the openstack metadata service to support peer discovery.
A GET on http://169.254.169.254/openstack/latest/peers.json returns a JSON
list of instances in the same project. This can be used to seed a node list
for a gossip protocol.

Change-Id: I76c912e7cd6c417b042567a55fb5869f5a22608e
Implements: blueprint first-discover-your-peers

commit_message:
implements:bp/fsl-sdn-os-mech-driver::fsl mech driver

Freescale SDN Mechanism Driver to support CRD service

Added new files,

ml2_conf_fslsdn.ini - ml2 fsl sdn mechanism driver configuration file
mech_fslsdn.py      - fslsdn Mechanism driver for ml2 plug-in
test_fslsdn_mech.py - unit test case for the new mechanism driver

Modified files,

setup.cfg - modified the file : added paths to ml2_conf_fslsdn.ini and
            fslsdn Mechanism driver class path.

Change-Id: I70cd2fd9a09784aac5d64371961d0dfb2f798b19

Implements: blueprint fsl-sdn-os-mech-driver

The following changes were in place.
[1] PEP8 based corrections to the codebase.
[2] CRD Service configurations options were added.
     modified:   neutron/common/config.py
[3] code modifications and PEP8 changes were done
     modified:   neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/mech_fslsdn.py
     modified:   neutron/tests/unit/ml2/drivers/test_fslsdn_mech.py

Change-Id: I92669eaa72ef766d763003c5fb0d34418b912f50

subject: DB: deleteion of an instance would not delete the system metadata
messages:
[{'account_id': 6172, 'date': '2014-02-02 17:18:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Hi Gary,
thanks for starting work on this
(I was already working around this bug https://review.openstack.org/#/c/56266/) 

Unfortunately I don't have enough time to finish work. So I would like to help you a bit and in introduce in approach that will work (because this one won't work) 

The problem (and why this issues is not fixed yet):
1) There are couple of methods that works with soft deleted instance.
That actually use instance_system_metadata. And we are using in instance_system_metadata as well soft deletion.

So when we are reading deleted instance we are join as usually only not soft deleted instance_system_metadata => so you will get empty set of metadata (in this case) => produce another bug..

The way to solve this problem is next: 
1) Always read all instance_system_metadata 
2) In instance_destroy use soft_delete
3) In instance_system_metedata (delete/set) use hard delete. 

(It will be not simple, but if you finish this work we will get as well some perfromance improvments (because we will reduce amount of instance_system_metadata records + remove one condition from JOIN)

I hope you will be able to finish this work! Thanks"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-02 17:21:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Doesn't seem to work

DB: deleteion of an instance would not delete the system metadata

instance is deleted.

commit_message:
Sync oslo.db.sqlalchemy

Closes-bug: #1276510

This patch syncs latest oslo.db code. The purpose of this sync is to
bring in a fix for an HA blocker issue.

b4f72b2 Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors
eff69ce Drop dependency on log from oslo db code
11f2add Clean up docstring in db.sqlalchemy.session
...

Change-Id: Ie81a2c4410856f9a1f07f8e8d8f193ef3c5f21b6

mask the mysql password from cinder.conf

password from the log output.  It converts the actual
password to 'xxx'.

commit_message:
Convert use_neutron_default_nets to BoolOpt

This option is boolean by nature, and setting it to StrOpt causes confusion.
For example, if you set this to 'true' in config file:

use_neutron_default_nets=true

then Nova will not use default nets, as string value is 'true', not 'True'.
Changing this to BoolOpt fixes this issue and makes the code more consistent.

Change-Id: Ib018fbff7a94af499dc1f44dab4f5353613cc721

commit_message:
Add audit period to instance notifications

This patch adds audit_period_{beginning,ending} to
compute.instance.create.{start,stop,error} and
compute.instance.delete.{start,stop} notifications,
which is consistent with other nova and OpenStack
notifications.

Closes-Bug: #1269494
Change-Id: Idd25871d1ee1663ff4e6eedf105c6bf1d4d47751

commit_message:
Change package action to :upgrade

To achieve both uniformity and least surprise, it might be better to
always upgrade packages.  Before this change, it only installed some,
upgraded others.

If noone disagrees, I will change these package resources to honor
platform overrides and the corresponding tests.  (Feedback welcome :)

Change-Id: Ia76886743efddc783c484faef2db3668a7d66768

commit_message:
Volume-Host affinity weight which uses Ceilometer

Added a new weight for the filter scheduler that gets data from
ceilometer, if available, and uses it to determine the host where a
volume is placed, allowing the weight to give a good score to this host
or a bad score to any other.

Change-Id: I0e6d052a63e728e16538de7e5229e3cda9b0cc8f
Implements: blueprint cross-service-filter-scheduling

Now in OpenStack nova, we support live migration, cold migration
and resize.

For live migration, we do not need to confirm after live migration
finished.

For resize, we need to confirm, as we want to give end user an
opportunity to rollback.

The problem is cold migration, because cold migration and resize
share same code path, so once admin submit a cold migration request
and after the cold migration finished, the VM will goes to
verify_resize state, and admin needs to confirm resize. Nova should
support auto confirm cold migration by default.

DocImpact

will only handle auto confirm for cold migration.

3) Default value is 0
4) resize_confirm_window will only handle auto confirm for resize

Implements bp auto-confirm-cold-migration

commit_message:
Auto confirm cold migration by default

Now in OpenStack nova, we support live migration, cold migration
and resize.

For live migration, we do not need to confirm after live migration
finished.

For resize, we need to confirm, as we want to give end user an
opportunity to rollback.

The problem is cold migration, because cold migration and resize
share same code path, so once admin submit a cold migration request
and after the cold migration finished, the VM will goes to
verify_resize state, and admin needs to confirm resize. Nova should
support auto confirm cold migration by default.

UpgradeImpact
DocImpact
A new parameter was introduced: cold_migration_confirm_window, it
will only handle auto confirm for cold migration.
1) Set to 0 to disable auto confirm to cold migration
2) Set to N to auto confirm cold migrations after N seconds
3) Default value is 1

Implements bp auto-confirm-cold-migration
Change-Id: I2d41a9267be27b109c22dea40b061967513353f8

commit_message:
Change index of brocade networks table from int to string

This migration changes the id field for the brocadenetworks
table from int to string (uuid). This brocade specific table
indexes using uuid.

Closes-Bug: #1271276

Change-Id: Ia5581f86d13e88df68b2c3eb283d3fe745a9d7c9

commit_message:
Make sure the path of default storage pool is used

Seed machine image got created at /var/lib/libvirt/images (the default
path for the default storage pool) even if this location has been
altered.

This patch ensures that the correct path is used, by checking the path
first.

Change-Id: I3e4ccff301524b8f08bba7099fafe5a9b4d3442c
Closes-Bug: #1276277

commit_message:
Remove asserts for optional imports

Horizon's __init__.py has some code that explicitly allows it to
be imported by setup.py before Django is set up, by making import
failures just throw a warning instead of an exception. But that code
is defeated by a bunch of asserts that were added later, that just
make the error even more confusing.

I'm removing the asserts and replacing them with __all__.

Closes-bug: #1210253
Change-Id: I0fde7810a033fd7216da9a5460f5e4e323b4d6e9
(cherry picked from commit b6eb9a2480a82cf93f7a62e9c7373feddc8296fe)

commit_message:
Added checking for slash of end in base_url

If don't check for slash at end of base_url, the error may occur
in tests because of appearance of a double slash in url.

Change-Id: I939d911e5114608cbde9d30cf0c4f435f2a2b7ac
Closes-Bug: #1271556

commit_message:
Migrate opt_in_group() and opt() to a fixture

Create a configuration fixture to support registering arbitrary
configuration options and migrate away from the use of
opt_in_group() and opt().  Most uses of opt_in_group() calls
from .setUp() were moved into moved into the .config() method on
the test case class.

Change-Id: I94fd57f4e24826f26c5ab09779f0583737a9737a
bp: keystone-parallel-testing

commit_message:
Devtest Overcloud all-in-one support.

If OVERCLOUD_ALL_IN_ONE is set builds the overcloud
by using a single image. This is useful if you want
to save memory or only have access to a single
bare metal overcloud machine.

This is something we've supported in the old TOCI scripts and
it has proven useful to some of us.

For now the all-in-one commands are all undocumented.

Change-Id: I392322b79b4635d77047f020bbd40e4a4676ac28

commit_message:
Midonet plugin, set __native_bulk_support correctly

__native_bulk_support was incorrectly set to False, thus the
unit tests handling bulk operations were skipped.
Added a fix for chains bulk create

Closes-bug: 1237412
Change-Id: I46ea0e4c2668e59ca787ae9e68fb8bf660312712

commit_message:
Make more dashboard options configurable

This change adds the following new attributes:

node['openstack']['dashboard']['password_autocomplete']
node['openstack']['dashboard']['neutron']['enable_lb']
node['openstack']['dashboard']['neutron']['enable_quotas']

Changing these will be reflected in the local_settings.py
configuration file.

Note that there are additional neutron options, however I've opted to
only do enable_lb and enable_quotas as we have a load balancer recipe
in the network cookbook, and enable_quotas defaults to True.  The
remaining neutron options can also be turned into attributes if/when we
support that functionality.

Change-Id: I6fd9f7df58f46861c6fa8d8c6ed502fb554d951e

commit_message:
External interface shows as up fake

On the network topology router-mouse-over-balloon, the list of
interfaces contains one labeled "fake<some_id>" which is a placeholder
for the external interface.

This interface should be labeled with a much less confusing tag.
"extern" or "gateway" seems much better.

Closes-Bug: #1273774

Change-Id: I873f80244757f573778abcac746c32c26732c8a9

commit_message:
Update how dashboard's secret key is handled

Currently, you can override the 'secret_key_path' attribute but this
does not get reflected in the dashboard configuration.  This change
does the following:

- updates local_settings.py to use the specified secret key
- adds a default attribute for 'secret_key_content' which when set
overrides the contents of the secret key (useful if you have multiple
web servers running dashboard and they all need the same secret key)

Change-Id: Ia82947280a64f6b1ec693ee273ac386a71be57ad
Closes-Bug: #1279863

I find (since python 2.6) Environment error is a more general exception to catch rather than worrying about the artificial differences between IOError, OSError, socket.error etc.
Often higher level functions might throw either IOError or OSError so catching Environment error is needed in that case.
Also with the exception hierarchy changes in python 3.3,
Environment error is merged with OSError and thus Environment error is the most cross python version compatible exception to catch.'}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-10-18 06:03:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Abandoned

commit_message:
report port number for address already in use errors

* nova/wsgi.py(Service.__init__): Catch external errors
(socket.error is a subclass of EnvironmentError since python 2.6),
and log the port number attempted to bind to.

commit_message:
Adds support for the get_rdp_console API

Hyper-V employs RDP to access virtual machine consoles, unlike most
other hypervisors which support VNC.

In order to support this scenario, the get_rdp_console API has been
added to Nova. This commit adds the corresponding client side feature,
implemented in a way consistent with existing VNC and SPICE console
support.

Nova Gerrit commit: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/43502/

Change-Id: I86b814797d234f1eb49a7fa67ed27a9bcda034ae
Implements: blueprint hyper-v-rdp-console

If the neutron server erroneously thinks than the l2 agent is down
it will fail to bind a port, which can lead to VM's spawn errors.

This patch aims to add support for agent checks flags.

Change-Id: If047c5d52d10a8ca9b1b765400bdd99a29550b1e
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

"}]
commit_message:
Tune up report and downtime intervals for l2 agent

If the neutron server erroneously thinks than the l2 agent is down
it will fail to bind a port, which can lead to VM's spawn errors.

This patch aims to add support for agent checks flags.

Change-Id: If047c5d52d10a8ca9b1b765400bdd99a29550b1e
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
(cherry picked from commit 30885efc1f7ee1b8490474399014f1f5c931097f)

commit_message:
Fixing neutron::server connection parameter

Previously, neutron::server's (deprecated) sql_connection parameter
had a default value, preventing the new/preferred connection
parameter from ever being used.

This change removes that default, permitting the connection
parameter to work properly, and extends unit tests to confirm.

bug introduced at commit 82552e79316a4ffc1c879dd3aaa1f4735a4a35a0,
change I300fc12092bca1abdd105e0c0c272f7fd49258ac

Change-Id: I116b482c620b5c44b88c1b801438a100343f6f9f
(cherry picked from commit af1fd0b6042c76fc48bae81d36a74b7a51d00fb7)

commit_message:
Use six.moves.urllib.parse instead of urlparse

To keep Python 3.x compatibility, use six.moves.urllib.parse to
replace urlparse.

Closes-Bug: #1279611
Change-Id: Ib91cf439777a11dd4d7ed4472014d17942f7de86

In novaclient/shell.py there is a parameter called 'password_fun'
which isn't defined anywhere. Also in novaclient/client.py there
is a method called 'password_func()' isn't defined. Both of them
are pointed to 'password_func' in novaclient/client.py
This patch fixes this bug.

Change-Id: Ibb8e95a2efc77575dcc8544584c708c5c62b7dea
"}, {'created': '2014-02-12 11:17:12.000000000', 'message': "Fix variable miss in novaclient

In novaclient/shell.py there is a variable called 'password_fun'
which isn't used anywhere.
It's a spelling miss, and should be modified to 'password_func'
to be used in novaclient/client.py
This patch fixes this bug.

Change-Id: Ibb8e95a2efc77575dcc8544584c708c5c62b7dea
"}, {'created': '2014-02-12 23:38:38.000000000', 'message': "Fix spelling miss of password_func variable

In novaclient/shell.py there is a variable called 'password_fun'
which isn't used anywhere.
In fact it's a spelling miss, and should be modified to 'password_func'
which is used in novaclient/client.py
This patch fixes this bug.

Change-Id: Ibb8e95a2efc77575dcc8544584c708c5c62b7dea
"}]
commit_message:
Fix spelling miss of password_func variable

In novaclient/shell.py there is a variable called 'password_fun'
which isn't used anywhere.
In fact it's a spelling miss, and should be modified to 'password_func'
which is used in novaclient/client.py
This patch fixes this bug.

Change-Id: Ibb8e95a2efc77575dcc8544584c708c5c62b7dea

commit_message:
Optionally enable file injection

There is a patch up for nova right now that disables file injection by default.
This is a corresponding devstack change that only sets file injection options if
it is enabled in the devstack config.  This is good to keep around so that we
can easily turn it on for testing.

The nova change is id Icff1304fc816acc843f8962727aef8bbbc7bbaa3.

Change-Id: I5015f2c351b1d680c205d7f9a5204febca490b91

a code move only with some updated comments.  The functions are now
sorted alphabetically within function groups, eg. all git-related functions
are grouped together.  The groups are listed at the top of the file.

'functions' sources 'functions-common' so no additional changes are required
for backward-compatability.

All functions shared with Grenade have also been moved.

functions-common was created from commit e0ed8ea038299952826b27a16753775472f108d8

commit_message:
Split functions

Move shared and non-DevStack-specific functions to `functions-common`.  This is
a code move only with some updated comments.  The functions are now
sorted alphabetically within function groups, eg. all git-related functions
are grouped together.  The groups are listed at the top of the file.

'functions' sources 'functions-common' so no additional changes are required
for backward-compatability.

All functions shared with Grenade have also been moved.

functions-common was created from commit e0ed8ea038299952826b27a16753775472f108d8

Change-Id: I73bf7134fd6a60ec1ea44a5bfab08b0569b60ded

commit_message:
Install glance images before starting Nova

The docker driver for Nova needs a registry service to be running.
It is being run inside a container using an image -- that image must
be downloaded. The registry service must be started via
nova_plugins/hypervisor-docker, but this is presently called
before Glance's image download.

The reordering is being done such that Glance may download the
registry image, but prior to starting Nova such that "hypervisor-docker"
may have an image downloaded and available to launch the registry.

This change should cause no negative effects on other hypervisors.

Change-Id: I7bccb42517e4c6187f2a90c64f39cda4577f89a3
blueprint: docker-glance-uploads

commit_message:
lvm: unhandled exception when migrating volume

Catches the StopIteration exception if the destination volume group
does not exist when attempting to migrate a volume.

Change-Id: I0b5dd15e4c7198fe54abf1aa917a60554adcd568
Closes-Bug:  #1277512

[{'created': '2014-02-06 15:04:50.000000000', 'message': 'Cleanup cinder-rootwrap support

cinder_rootwrap support in devstack handled a number of now-abandoned
use cases:

- no $CINDER_DIR/etc/cinder/rootwrap.d (old-style rootwrap)
- using oslo-rootwrap instead of cinder-rootwrap (abandoned experiment)

This change removes unused code paths and aligns
configure_cinder_rootwrap() with configure_nova_rootwrap().

Change-Id: I387808dae0e064cc9c894c74ab78e86124f08dd2
'}]
commit_message:
Cleanup cinder-rootwrap support

cinder_rootwrap support in devstack handled a number of now-abandoned
use cases:

- no $CINDER_DIR/etc/cinder/rootwrap.d (old-style rootwrap)
- using oslo-rootwrap instead of cinder-rootwrap (abandoned experiment)

This change removes unused code paths and aligns
configure_cinder_rootwrap() with configure_nova_rootwrap().

Change-Id: I387808dae0e064cc9c894c74ab78e86124f08dd2

commit_message:
Move install responsibilities to domU

As we are moving forward to test XenAPI in the gate, it is necessary to
move dom0 related modifications to be performed from domU. For this
purpose, a new user is created, and that user should be used to talk to
dom0 from domU. This change creates that user, makes it possible for
dom0 to log in to domU with that account, and configure that account to
be able to talk down to dom0.

Also move several steps to the nova xenserver plugin:
 - dom0 plugin installation
 - create kernels and images directory
 - install console rotate script
 - configure a cron to execute console rotate script

Configuration changes:
    A new configuration option, DOMZERO_USER has been created, that
    specifies a user account that is configured to be able to do
    passwordless ssh to dom0.

Change-Id: If9de0b297a67b7cdb5de78d8dd0e8b2ca578b601

commit_message:
Add tests for oauth consumer normalize fields

There were no tests that verified that fields in oauth consumers
were normalized as expected. The tests show that the fields aren't
being normalized as expected on update.

Change-Id: I3bc95766b61d8dc8c85b32f628b275721255e95d
Related-Bug: #1276857

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary check to see if trustee exists

Previously we check if the returned trustee value is None, this
is already done at the backend level.

Change-Id: I801bed09300782e289ee505612df09f7270fcb4e

is incorrect.

[{'created': '2014-02-10 14:27:59.000000000', 'message': 'Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I0661b20a0e426fee56bc706d364dfe158da9be72
Closes-Bug: #1277495
'}]
commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I0661b20a0e426fee56bc706d364dfe158da9be72
Closes-Bug: #1277495

commit_message:
Revert the tempest service name to marconi

This patch is to rollback the change introduced by
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/73100/. 73100 is no longer needed
because of the recent https://review.openstack.org/#/c/69497/.
Using 'marconi' as the service name will keep us aligned with the
naming convention used by other projects.

Change-Id: I5da6d2aaeb5c9dc29a1cbc70c8425449807eb34c

commit_message:
Marconi fixes for precise

Fix a couple of problems found on Ubuntu:
* $MARCONI_DIR/etc/marconi/policy.json doesn't exist; removed the copy to /etc/marconi
* added a seting of nssize in /etc/mongodb.conf for Ubuntu
* restart the correct serice name on Ubuntu

Change-Id: I9bd2ab1aa4fb94ff96559e069e5b62138c358fb5

commit_message:
Raise requirement of Pep8 to 1.4.6

Pep8 1.4.6 has been released and can be required for Icehouse.
There are some noteworthy changes:

* Fix false positive E261/E262 when the file contains a BOM
* Fix E701, E702 and E703 not detected sometimes
* Fix E122 not detected in some cases. (Issue #201 and #208)
* Fix false positive E121 with multiple brackets. (Issue #203)

Change-Id: I99109e83ab46e4db19e27db0711752b34d5084a0

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 rescue API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: I3d08bc20e4c585dca1e218e8d97b208d158a3096

commit_message:
Adding Mako>=0.4.0 to global requirements

Mako>=0.4.0 is default template engine that is used by Pecan.
As well it is in requirements of Pecan:
https://github.com/stackforge/pecan/blob/master/requirements.txt#L2
So it makes sense to add it to global requirements, so we will be
able to use it in other projects without Pecan.

Change-Id: Id7b67a28c882ef00d255118f717857dd3d7021c5

commit_message:
Provide clearer error when deleting enabled domain

Currently the message is confusing, because it reads like an instruction
to delete an enabled domain, rather than an instruction that you can
only delete disabled domains.  Hopefully this wording is a little clearer
for users.

Change-Id: I5189cd1bbae0e485d03660be19f20879110a3b3e
Closes-Bug: #1279823

[{'created': '2014-02-06 20:21:04.000000000', 'message': 'Fix cinder-backup volume restore with ceph driver

Restore operations currently break if restoring to
the backup source volume and that volume is an rbd
that has had incremental backups performed on it.

Change-Id: Ieafe6ab2d1a15cad2b534a3aab0df29eb8591306
Closes-Bug: 1276977
'}, {'created': '2014-02-08 13:50:25.000000000', 'message': 'Fix cinder-backup volume restore with ceph driver

Restore operations currently break if restoring to
the backup source volume, that volume is an rbd and
the associated backup was incremental.

Change-Id: Ieafe6ab2d1a15cad2b534a3aab0df29eb8591306
Closes-Bug: 1276977
'}]
commit_message:
Fix cinder-backup volume restore with ceph driver

Restore operations currently break if restoring to
the backup source volume, that volume is an rbd and
the associated backup was incremental.

Change-Id: Ieafe6ab2d1a15cad2b534a3aab0df29eb8591306
Closes-Bug: 1276977

commit_message:
Verify that parsed environment file maps to a dict

An internal unexpected exception is raised while create a stack with an
environment file which only has string content. We should handle the case
and raise the correct error message such as "The environment is not YAML
mapping".

Change-Id: If1ca86fb4e05751908459bcb80d6e3a00f7b06f6
Closes-Bug: #1279609

commit_message:
Switch over to oslosphinx

Having the sphinx theme in the same namespace package
as the production code has been causing issues with
devstack installations. The solution settled on was
to rename oslo.sphinx to oslosphinx because oslo.sphinx
is not a "production" library.

See the linked bug report for more background details.

Closes-Bug: #1277168
Change-Id: I220b8901cef36499e91b92719f1e8e5461a95e92

subject: Switch over to oslosphinx

commit_message:
Switch over to oslosphinx

Having the sphinx theme in the same namespace package
as the production code has been causing issues with
devstack installations. The solution settled on was
to rename oslo.sphinx to oslosphinx because oslo.sphinx
is not a "production" library.

See the linked bug report for more background details.

Closes-Bug: #1277168
Change-Id: I419fe50d66fa0c1ac48deca2286ae7c4b922d72d

[{'created': '2014-02-13 23:00:00.000000000', 'message': "Fix tee statement for catching tempest output

The use of exec and tee doesn't seem to be quite right, and was
unreliable in terms of catching the exit status of the tempest
test as well as not catching the output when things went wrong.

This changes the way we do the redirect and the tee to something
that should be more robust and seems to work reliably in testing.

Change-Id: Ieb9d725839fb8e3f9e2e63a2b7b2e9c7c86713a2
"}]
commit_message:
Fix tee statement for catching tempest output

The use of exec and tee doesn't seem to be quite right, and was
unreliable in terms of catching the exit status of the tempest
test as well as not catching the output when things went wrong.

This changes the way we do the redirect and the tee to something
that should be more robust and seems to work reliably in testing.

Change-Id: Ieb9d725839fb8e3f9e2e63a2b7b2e9c7c86713a2

commit_message:
Avoid use of str() with exceptions

The new Message class does not allow str() so all locales can be safely
translated. It requires use of unicode() instead.

Change-Id: I1fd9142b0211cecc746578f4080cb2ddfa663b0d
Related-Bug: #1274638

Fix unused puppet agent/master logging templates

commit_message:
Remove no longer needed generation of the virtual-power-key

With the recent change to inject the powerkey into the image (e401ef4f)
os-refresh-config does not need to generate a key anymore.

Change-Id: Ie253cac1fc189e226995ddcff16eeb24b321ddc4

hi Joe,

just realised the oslo.messaging work. so notifier middleware is being moved to oslo.messaging (https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Oslo/GraduationStatus#notifier. it's dependent on openstack/common/rpc code right now). so this patch is going to fail. 

there's also work to move audit middleware to oslo.middleware but i need to check with dhellmann on the status of that. (https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Oslo/GraduationStatus#audit)

so i guess the notifier middleware currently will be replaced with the notifier middleware oslo.messaging once that work is done. i don't know how you want to act on this? maybe make adjustments once the code has been graduated to the right place?"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-12 22:13:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Doesn't seem to work

gordon,

I am happy as long as this code works, but the status quo is not acceptable. Thoughts?'}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2014-02-13 17:22:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Joe, completely agree with you. this code needs to be fixed. just checking with dhellmann and jd on the timeline of graduation and i'll update you once i hear back.

my goal is to get this working for Icehouse one way or another. :)"}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-02-13 17:29:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

thanks, I would much rather see this work then get removed too.'}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2014-02-13 19:39:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

hi Joe,

just an update on oslo.graduation process. i've spoken with dhellmann and the oslo.middleware graduation may or may not be ready for Icehouse. because of that, we've come up with an alternative.

notifier middleware will continue to be graduated to oslo.messaging. a oslo.messaging compatible copy of audit middleware will be move to openstack/pyCADF library. that way if projects have migrated to oslo.messaging. thye can use middleware in pyCADF and if not, they can use middleware in oslo-incubator.

i'm still trying out this process so maybe hold off on dropping code for a bit but if all works as plan we can remove openstack.common.middleware code while keeping the pyCADF requirement. thoughts?"}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-02-13 23:41:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

sounds good to me, once that is done I would like to actually enable this in the gate as well. I would like to see more ceilometer/nova integration testing in the gate.'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-02-13 23:42:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned

commit_message:
Make nova_ipam_lib use Network, FixedIP, and FloatingIP objects

This makes nova_ipam_lib use objects for almost everything except
for VIF-related functions, which is coming soon.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: Ib39bbc86921eeb849e715a205dccaab3aad6d1c6

commit_message:
Make ironic-api not single threaded

The ironic-api service is an instance of wsgiref
simple_server.WSGIServer.  This derives from SocketServer.TCPServer,
which requires that SocketServer.ThreadingMixIn be mixed in for it to
become thread'able, however this was not being done when starting the
WSGIServer.

This patch creates a ThreadedSimpleServer class, which is just a mix
of ThreadingMixIn and WSGIServer, so that the ironic-api process
does not block on network IO.

Change-Id: I9d686765edb4975519840a51d3beeb2be797a4fa
Related-bug: #1279206

commit_message:
Make nova-network use FixedIP for timeouts

This makes nova-network manager use the FixedIP object when
disassociating addresses due to timeout.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I909f710543239207f6d27230b527b4495a23f2cb

[{'created': '2014-02-11 08:55:02.000000000', 'message': 'Raises BadRequest for grant_access on ignore_dbs

Reasons:
- Currently, it just logs an informative log in guestagent log, and then
  control shifts to next line, which provides the requested grant.
- This brings the need to raise the exception instead of informative
  logging.

Changes:
- Raises BadRequest if ignore_dbs are requested access instead of
  informative logging into guest-agent logs.

Change-Id: I9df08d04cd42916f3d1f91e05cd4799bb9041eae
Closes-Bug: #1257021
'}]
commit_message:
Raises BadRequest for grant_access on ignore_dbs

Reasons:
- Currently, it just logs an informative log in guestagent log, and then
  control shifts to next line, which provides the requested grant.
- This brings the need to raise the exception instead of informative
  logging.

Changes:
- Raises BadRequest if ignore_dbs are requested access instead of
  informative logging into guest-agent logs.

Change-Id: I9df08d04cd42916f3d1f91e05cd4799bb9041eae
Closes-Bug: #1257021

commit_message:
Make nova-network use FixedIP object for updates

This makes nova-network manager use the FixedIP object for
updates instead of direct database calls.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: Ia191148cf7510ffdb0fbd4186fa34bb4c5ab1b0f
