commit_message:
Change description of oldest reviews

Make it more clear that the list of oldest reviews is just that, and not call it
a variant of calculating the longest waiting reviews.

Change-Id: I890f07519ceccfc57a5a73293817105a3b8c9f53

commit_message:
Fix task_manager acquire post landing for c4f2f26ed

In original implementation we used context lib with try/finally
to make sure release_resources will be called even if there was an
exception inside acquire_resources. With c4f2f26ed we broke that
functionality, so this patch intended to fix this.

Closes-Bug: #1279992
Change-Id: I04abc67aedc226bc126b1d93901c71bcd8a5bf15

commit_message:
Make nova-network use FixedIP object for disassociations

This makes nova-network mananger use the FixedIP object for
disassociating IPs.

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: Ia0a38bbd31cc22095893bff89bcaa402a9bc2722

commit_message:
Removing unused get_node_power_state

There is a periodic task that is used to check the power state and save it to
the DB. Users can query the DB instead of checking the machine.

Change-Id: I918132854a0b4eb9aa302aeea85b3267470c20c0
Closes-Bug: #1277062

This is actually not what migration is for. If something must happen
before a service is started, that is a post configuration thing that we
should order before enabling/starting/restarting the service.

Os-refresh-config will be changed to run migration after post-configure,
since it is for on-line things, not offline things.

'}]
commit_message:
Move cinder-volume creation to post-configure

This is actually not what migration is for. If something must happen
before a service is started, that is a post configuration thing that we
should order before enabling/starting/restarting the service.

Os-refresh-config will be changed to run migration after post-configure,
since it is for on-line things, not offline things.

Change-Id: I2c4eccab3010ec91fcd8129951f638b37bc0932a

commit_message:
Remove multipart/form-data file upload

The requests 'files' parameter adds this 'Content-Type: multipart/form-data'
HTTP header and the whole multipart body data get stored with the object.
This also create a memory hog issue because files are loaded in memory before
being actually sent. This patch removes this behavior and restores what was
done before, ie: direct uploading.

This patches also fixes an issue in requests, when used with glance
CooperativeReader it mis-calculates content-length leading to chunked encoding
for raw upload.

Change-Id: Ie5b0a1078bedd33f09c6157f48b5f88116c589fa
Closes-Bug: #1280072
Closes-Bug: #1280275

commit_message:
Fix building of image-api-v2

Due to moving files around in the directory, openstack-doc-test did not
generate the markdown document correctly.

Adjust the test for checking that we build image-api-v2 for the
repository renames.

'}, {'account_id': 1192, 'date': '2014-02-07 22:11:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

I think it would be really great if tempest configuration itself could go in tempest rather than rally. Here is what I think it should do: 

1. Query the deployment and create what users/images/networks/flavors/etc that tempest is expecting if not already present.
2. Query the deployment for available services. This may be tricky since I don't think all of OpenStack is yet auto-discoverable.
3. Create the files on the local machine that tempest expects. There are a lot of options in tempest that refer to files and these files are not installed as part of tempest.

Also the current format of the tempest.conf.sample file that is autogenerated is not friendly for substitution. We should change that or generate an additional file during generation that is more templated. We really don't want a separately maintained copy of the template somewhere else."}, {'account_id': 8408, 'date': '2014-02-11 16:18:27.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-11 16:18:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

commit_message:
Rally & Tempest integration (base) - part 1

Use tempest (https://github.com/openstack/tempest) inside rally to
organize base for verification functionality & for benchmarks scenario
based on tempest.

This patch adds ability to install Tempest tests (no parameters needs)
and to verify the specified cloud (takes a deploy_id as parameter, this
parameter is now optional). For now, there are smoke tests.

Usage:
rally-manage tempest install - install tempest tests
rally verify start --deploy-id=<deploy_id> - start cloud verification

Change-Id: I70bb37476dd2d12370ea77156adab3ceaddb93cb
Related: blueprint tempest-verification

commit_message:
Look for local.json in preference to config.json.

We've had a long standing ugliness where config.json was edited by
devtest to set the ssh username, and then when one commits a
tripleo-image-elements change, it would include your username. This is
undesirable :).

Change-Id: I3129bf638e519f2b03a05cae482e26fd5aef40b1

commit_message:
Remove rootwrap from incubator

oslo.rootwrap now fully graduated to a standalone library, and all three
consuming projects (Nova, Cinder and Neutron) use the library as of the
Icehouse release. There is no need to maintain the frozen code copy in
oslo-incubator anymore.

Implements bp remove-rootwrap

Change-Id: I522bb982f51472a2902ee9b0b7ade1d18351962b

commit_message:
Install syslinux in nova-barmetal

Previously the element relied on nova installing syslinux
before implicitely, which was not always the case in package
install mode. Move it to the place where it is used instead.

commit_message:
Standalone servers for keepalive and receiver

 - added supervisor sections for assassind and receiverd
 - keepalive renamed to assasin (name conflicts) and starts as separate process controlled by supervisor
 - RPC receiver moved to separate server

NOTICE: depends on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72325/

Change-Id: Ib7c74a2b3304cdb5a7c4dbaa57bcbf776b80dcfa
Implements: blueprint nailgun-move-to-uwsgi

commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I840f950d2e9f6e1e40af578900e92cedf8f14295
Closes-Bug: #1277495

commit_message:
Implementing streaming MapReduce jobs

Adding support for new dotted job type MapReduce.Streaming.
The new job type will let the dashboard know to display some
job configuration items that are only applicable to this new
job type.

Implements:  blueprint dashboard-edp-streaming-mapreduce

Change-Id: Ia3ebaf41b3f153b927002dc2350af79bc7d86747

Add cpu-{node,mem,disk} to the testenv JSON

devtest in Ibc61c8e062833d56090559057d8b3aa38a42d275 will expect to see
node-cpu, node-mem, and node-disk in the JSON datafile, so add the
defaults in.

commit_message:
Temporarily cap swiftclient version to fix glance gate failure

Recent python-swiftclient 2.0 release caused wide range gate failure,
due to glance failed to update image to swift backend store. And then vm
refuse to boot with corrupted image, and then massive devstack failure.

Temporarily cap swiftclient version to revive gate jobs until proper
fix.

Related-bug: 1280072
Change-Id: I0604594a0ccc04cfcf120c1004ac63d1cc7c8e14

commit_message:
Treating blanked out config values as defaults for cluster templates

If a dashboard user blanks out a value on the service config tabs
of the cluster-template creation form, the dashboard treats those
as their default values rather than an empty config (which causes
errors).

Fixes:  bug #1212354

Change-Id: If4b720045e78e1d65156c03f75a0cc93706d9015

commit_message:
Run tests in parallel as much as possible

The rpc unit tests have dependencies between tests that make it
impossible to run them in parallel right now, and because that
module is deprecated it doesn't make sense to spend a lot of
effort fixing the problems.  In order to test the other modules
in parallel, we now do two test runs: one in parallel for
everything but rpc, and one serialized for rpc.

Closes-Bug: #1272035

Change-Id: I85ae00b0180bb6fdc760c97882e4e7901e9db2ef

Rename TestEngine --> BenchmarkEngine

commit_message:
Rename EXTRA_ELEMENTS to SEED_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS

In boot-seed-vm we had a special variable that wasn't consistent with
the rest of devtest - it was only used there, not for other images we
build, and without namespaceing thats at best confusing. Also
cloud-init-nocloud is required for the seed, so there was no point
having it be optional.

Change-Id: Iecfba0cfa495c03c1d3e0495ec38274ee6407ab6

commit_message:
Teach cache-url to handle file:// URIs.

We can now support file:// URIs in source-repositories files and other
places, by ignoring curl's inability to determine an HTTP status code
for them.

Change-Id: Ie226ce05ecb912b23cedc73fd7ba53c0b9c0fe35

As i understood the reason we are skiping online check for provisioning is that node can be booted by ipmi.

But why we should skip in case of separate deployment?'}, {'account_id': 8749, 'date': '2014-02-14 09:04:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Dmitry, the reason is separate provisioning/deployment was created for fuel hackers who wants to have full control.

And for this cases we want to disable all validation to not prevent user to run deployment, we have fragile status node detection system (with separate thread, and timeouts) in case if node is really offline (node can has offline status and it can be accessible via mcollective at the same time), orchestrator will report an error status for this node, but we must send this data to orchestrator.

Example of this problem you can see in bug report, our QA team use this feature and they faced with this problem.

Also rally team will use the same method for deployment.'}, {'account_id': 8907, 'date': '2014-02-14 09:26:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

commit_message:
Moved online node checking to before validation task

Here we are fixing two problems

* when we deploy cluster where we have
  offline nodes, we don't want to lock
  cluster's settings
* we should skip all validation in case
  of separate deployment/provisioning

Closes-bug: #1279790
Closes-bug: #1260629
Change-Id: If59940c6bd350e9a74daf9da2efafcba2f583099

commit_message:
Remove glance_notifications from notification_topic

The default notification_topic in Glance has been changed from
'glance_notifications' to 'notifications' in grizzly-2.

Ceilometer was configured to also listen on the
'glance_notifications' notification_topic in addition to
'notifications' to patch this bug. It shouldn't anymore.

Change-Id: I3d797c7e849319a1e20ef3ecbf158e8b8579d450
Closes-bug: #1273876
(cherry picked from commit 924f18ffae174847d4c3d5ec5d5ae4241c9dd897)

commit_message:
Add more escaping when writing the JSON datafile

ed7e22e04909c6f94223e0ba5d9ee06d7d84960f introduced two more keys and
values into the testenv JSON, but the double quotes are not escaped.
Escape them.

Change-Id: Ia2ff2d137f28ed84ec9254fa1d6698bb5c9d7a7a

'}, {'account_id': 1247, 'date': '2014-02-13 15:21:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I think it's a bad idea to diverge further from Nova's code

My understanding about why the Ironic team didn't first copy this code into oslo-incubator was that they planned to not diverge from Nova: http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-December/021065.html

It looks like Ironic hasn't synced changes from Nova since Nova commit a9bed2bab9a917ef288872d0f660e9f414281dc1

This copy-paste-diverge tendency causes technical debt to accumulate fast

I urge you all to (a) don't diverge further from Nova, (b) sync more recent changes from Nova, (c) get any small changes you need into Nova (e.g. a way to disable dict-like access) and, finally, (c) start using oslo-incubator to work with Nova folks to get this into a library that both projects can re-use"}, {'account_id': 2889, 'date': '2014-02-13 15:48:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Mark, thanks for calling me on what I committed to :)

If you and Dan feel that moving the object code into Oslo is a reasonable thing to do at this time, let's do it. If not, let's plan on doing it at the start of Juno.

Mikhail, I think it's OK for us to merge the prior patches which are making our object accessing consistently non-dict-based, but as Mark has pointed out, we shouldn't change the base object class - we should be staying in sync with Nova."}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2014-02-13 19:13:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Get rid object model `dict` methods part 6

Currently unified object model supports dict-like behavior of objects.
This behavior will be removed in the future so it's necessary to
change Ironic's code to use object attributes as attributes instead of
dictionary keys.

We don't actually remove the interface due to that Oslo might
introduce UOM in future together with this methods and we hide dict
interface from the objects since it has been deprecated.

Change-Id: Ib8662dd9950d5745dd390127b6954dd06c004eab
Closes-Bug: #1256260

commit_message:
Temporarily cap swiftclient version to fix upload error

Recent python-swiftclient 2.0 release caused wide range gate failure,
due to glance failed to update image to swift backend store. And then vm
refuse to boot with corrupted image, and then massive devstack failure.

Temporarily cap swiftclient version to revive gate jobs until proper
fix.

Change-Id: Ia282c21136cca55a018e8ccf3b02f97fcd2e1f28
Partial-Bug: 1280072

commit_message:
Horizon performance tuning

Closes-Bug: #1277292

Some optimizations for Apache/WSGI settings aimed to improve
Apache and Horizon performance:
    - Apache MPM switched from 'prefork' to 'event' for RH-like
      systems
    - Apache/WSGI parameters configuration based on server's
      hardware

Change-Id: Idbd3ccaf05d9ad4a1e8206facece0c53a3fd90e7

commit_message:
Temporary cap to python-keystoneclient due to test breakage

The latest 0.6.0 keystoneclient release breaks our test mocking,
so temporarily cap the version required to avoid gate breakage
while we work out the solution.

Partial-Bug: #1279907

[{'created': '2014-02-10 18:08:12.000000000', 'message': 'Specify CIDR netmask for each VIP

Explicitly setting the netmask for each VIP works around a bug
in Pacemaker where an incorrect netmask is calculated. This
subsequently sets an incorrect broadcast address.

Change-Id: Icf208eff1be27765611500ae0e71ead122a7c4ce
Closes-bug: #1277614
'}]
commit_message:
Specify CIDR netmask for each VIP

Explicitly setting the netmask for each VIP works around a bug
in Pacemaker where an incorrect netmask is calculated. This
subsequently sets an incorrect broadcast address.

Change-Id: Icf208eff1be27765611500ae0e71ead122a7c4ce
Closes-bug: #1277614

commit_message:
Port to oslo.messaging

* Remove openstack.common.rpc module and implement oslo.messaging
usage instead of that.
* Remove openstack.common.notifier (except api) as it is part of
oslo.messaging now.
* Remove zmq_receiver as a part of oslo.messaging too.

Implements: blueprint oslo-messaging
Change-Id: I4855826b2435b96bcf22ada239d17fa6d0837184

Now we maintain a list of pending operations which is backed up in admin metadata. A periodic task reviews the list and removes volume copies whose copy operation completed. When Cinder comes up, we check the admin metadata and rebuild the list.

commit_message:
If Cinder crashes during a migration or retype (where data is moved and
the operation can take a long time), the storage ends up with multiple
copies of the same volume which requires storage admin intervention. Now
we maintain a list of pending operations which is backed up in admin
metadata. A periodic task reviews the list and removes volume copies
whose copy operation completed. When Cinder comes up, we check the admin
metadata and rebuild the list.

Change-Id: I27df5cfa0b0af67f8c45bc3f73a436a5d3afca50
Closes-Bug: #1278035

commit_message:
VMware: improve performance when using get_vm_ref_from_name

The aforementioned method is used in the following cases:
1. When a instance is deleted
2. When a rescue instance is created or used

In patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60259/ the unique VM
name was saved on the config spec so that the VM ref can be accessed
via FindAllByUuid. This change makes use of that when the VM is to
be accessed by the name.

In addition to using the FindAllByUuid the VM ref is also cached
according to the unique VM name.

When a VM is deleted the cache is purged for the vm_name and UUID.

Change-Id: I1f00f8711713a41bb99e9a4fd9c78f68755eee25

commit_message:
Implements checking ring file existence on recon

When checking ring md5 integrity with swift recon if ring
file does not exist, swift-recon will give a stack trace.
This change will check if file exists, if ring file is not
found will print out url of server the ring file was not found on.

Change-Id: I7daafdb0aa6016038d08be5e92092bca60997a8a

commit_message:
Add assertRaisesRegexp method to common test.py

The assertRaisesRegexp method was added to unittest framework in
python 2.7, so we need similar method to use it in python 2.6
environment.

Add assertRaisesRegexp method which asserts that message
in a raised Exception matches a regexp.

commit_message:
API tests for neutron metering label and rules

Tests the following operations:

    1. create a metering label
    2. list metering labels
    3. show created metering label
    4. delete created metering label
    5. create a metering label rule
    6. list metering label rules
    7. show created metering label rule
    8. delete created metering label rule

part of blueprint: neutron-metering-labels-and-rules-api-test

Change-Id: Ib1391312429bf5fc7e061324b09b5d173ee6e301

commit_message:
Transition to alembic migration with oslo migration tool

1.Extends heat-manage usage for alembic common commands
For reference refer to: https://alembic.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api.html
2. Compatible with old usage
   heat-manage db_sync - will upgrade database
   heat-manage db_version
3. Improve tests coverage for heat-manage cmd util
4. Create sqlite database for tests from metadata
   sqlite doesnot support alter statements, and sqlalchemy-migrate was
   was patched to do that

Change-Id: Ifdee3c65c3d15bf84eaa68e0e45342b10670bb73
oslo-incubator: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/59433/
Blueprint: oslo-migration-toolkit

commit_message:
Add run pollsters on demand function to api

* Create new controller - pollsters
* Api publish rpc message with target 'run_pollsters' for agents
* Agents start all pollsters

Implements: blueprint run-all-pollsters-on-demand

commit_message:
Validate target host by scheduler

This patch adds the ability to check if the target host passes
filters before live migration.

Co-Author: Yassine Lamgarchal <yassine.lamgarchal@enovance.com>

Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration
Change-Id: Iec6e66651a64dd468cbb1ae714f230adf16a8b7e

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-15 13:30:29.000000000', 'message': 'Sync latest oslo db code to cinder

Changes from oslo-incubator
=====================================================

Change ID If5a73cb6: Remove "vim: tabstop=4 shiftwidth=4 softtabstop=4" from headers
Change ID If6e10268: Fix database connection string is secret
Change ID I9043bf2f: Removed copyright from empty files
Change ID I5254a51b: Fix the obsolete exception message
Change ID Iafa8509a: Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
Change ID If6187a0f: Removal of _REPOSITORY global variable.
Change ID I8407db72: Remove string.lowercase usage
Change ID I6fa140f2: Remove eventlet tpool from common db.api
Change ID I2960435c: Database hook enabling traditional mode at MySQL
Change ID I9356d176: Replace xrange in for loop with range
Change ID I86e9673a: SQLAlchemy error patterns improved
Change ID Ia89d749f: Remove unused import
Change ID I2000a02d: Correct invalid docstrings
Change ID I02fc3d96: Remove start index 0 in range()
Change ID I236408be: Make _extra_keys a property of ModelBase
Change ID Id79bca98: Fix violations of H302:import only modules
Change ID I5563360b: Enables db2 server disconnects to be handled pessimistically
Change ID Ic3dd4ec7: db.sqlalchemy.session add [sql].idle_timeout
Change ID I90be8797: Use six.iteritems to make dict work on Python2/3
Change ID Id5ff507c: Drop dependency on processutils from oslo db code
Change ID I333b8330: Fix locking in migration tests
Change ID I5675f3f6: Incorporating MIT licensed code
Change ID I7a4e72ee: Typos fix in db and periodic_task module
Change ID I13cfd5e9: Use six.moves.configparser instead of ConfigParser
Change ID I33f1566d: fix typo in db session docstring
Change ID Ic5d3cfe8: The ability to run tests at various backend
Change ID I31fe047a: Use log.warning() instead of log.warn() in oslo.db
Change ID Ic6f0c0ef: Remove vim header
Change ID I9ef2bf16: Use py3kcompat urlutils functions instead of urlparse
Change ID Iee0b3cf5: Don't use deprecated module commands
Change ID I51178d5b: Remove sqlalchemy-migrate 0.7.3 patching
Change ID I7e3c5e1e: Drop dependency on lockutils from oslo db code

commit_message:
Add the ability to get notified of connection loss

When joining a group it is common that the entity
joining that group would like to know if it has somehow
lost that group membership if certain conditions such
as disconnection occur, to accomodate this allow for the
driver to have a list of callbacks which will be automatically
called if the connection is lost.

Change-Id: Iab6acbc6b2934998e51f0618ec66962d77a6ce1c

commit_message:
Use reload from imp module for Python 3 compat

The reload function used to be a built-in in Python 2, but was changed
in Python 3 to be a function of the imp module. That change was
backported to Python 2.6, so it can be accessed from there across all
supported versions.

Change-Id: If37fc0b900f4e289dd8c2633df30e2bf4282d0a9

@Michael, the logic of prune is as following:
1) Get old compute node stats and new compute node stats
2) If old compute node stat metrics in new compute node stats, then pop out the old metrics and update it with new value
3) If set prune as true, then delete the metrics in the left old compute node stats.

So current logic already make sure duplicate values can be updated. This patch just want to make sure that admin can make some configuration to decide if to prune the old metrics or not.

You can refer to https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L637 for more detail.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-06 09:07:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: No score

commit_message:
Make prune compute_node_stats configurable

Nova compute manager will periodically prune metrics for
compute_node_stats, if there are some metrics did not update on
time, those metrics will be pruned.

For some cases, always prune metrics is not acceptable. i.e. I put
some metrics which only need update once to compute_node_stats and
want compute_node_stats keep this value for me. But those metrics
were always pruned by periodic task.

DocImpact
This patch was adding a parameter prune_compute_node_stats to decide
if prune compute_node_stats periodically or not, default value is
True.

commit_message:
warning log for default value (ext3) of default_ephemeral_format

ext3 has a bad proformance compared with ext4, we should use ext4 as
default instead. Before changing that, this patch throw a warning is for
backward compatibility.

Change-Id: I9814f7631dc5723d9857762e5507d5077721557d
Closes-bug: #1266262

The method 'utils.create_models_from_data' should have been
used to avoid duplications of code

commit_message:
Add sqlalchemy objects for the 'operation' resource

Added sqlalchemy objects for operation, and also migration script
for alembic.

Last modifications in this patchset were done to match the last
comments on this review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/69498/13

Change-Id: If3db0e2a8f646d8ee197198d206ac548879263b5

commit_message:
Refactor if logic in periodic_task

Currently we are checking twice whether spacing is None.
Since due-now is always smaller than spacing we can combine the two
if statements.

Change-Id: Icd354c8f9dd9988c9c985283abee7c852d2c13b2

commit_message:
Use timestamp in periodic tasks

All time related data in periodic tasks are in seconds.
Therefore creating datetime objects only adds overhead to the module.
This patch replaces all datetime objects with utc timestamps in periodic_tasks.
Changes to test scripts were made accordingly.

Change-Id: I5bf77fba26aac62856fe30585577b7cf66dd6257

commit_message:
Update policy check on services V3 API & DB layer

Remove db layer admin authorization for services and let
the admin to decide the policy setting.
Split the v3 API services authorization according to their actions
and add test cases for the policy check.

Change-Id: I1a63c0d9c6e29234390f4bb525deb9c69cbb3d90
Implements: blueprint v3-api-policy

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-28 23:15:13.000000000', 'message': "Remove glance_notifications from notification_topic

The default notification_topic in Glance has been changed from
'glance_notifications' to 'notifications' in grizzly-2.

Ceilometer was configured to also listen on the
'glance_notifications' notification_topic in addition to
'notifications' to patch this bug. It shouldn't anymore.

commit_message:
Remove glance_notifications from notification_topic

The default notification_topic in Glance has been changed from
'glance_notifications' to 'notifications' in grizzly-2.

Ceilometer was configured to also listen on the
'glance_notifications' notification_topic in addition to
'notifications' to patch this bug. It shouldn't anymore.

Change-Id: I3d797c7e849319a1e20ef3ecbf158e8b8579d450
Closes-bug: #1273876

commit_message:
Permit setting a /etc/hosts entry for the API.

This is needed for hypervisors to talk to Neutron etc without
undercloud DNS, when using SSL.

Change-Id: I30a7b9435120ea175b5a87b3d1cd0e1ce3154aad

Thanks for your patch.

(See the more recent comments around SSL compression and performance, and also links to recent urllib3 changes here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/33473)

Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 9311, 'date': '2014-02-03 14:10:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

Hi Stuart,

looking at wireshark, ssl compression looks disabled for requests 2.2.1 and 1.1.0 with python 2.7.5:
  In the Client Hello packet, the only compression method is null (0)
  Also, https://www.howsmyssl.com/a/check says that tls_compression_supported is False

Note that my test environment is ubuntu-13.10 which include openssl-1.0.1e-3ubuntu1.1.

This is very confusing, I thought this wouldn't be the case yet."}, {'account_id': 455, 'date': '2014-02-03 14:58:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Thanks Tristan.

I wonder if SSL is disabled globally on your test system?
To check you can try the following:

create a server.key and server.crt with the following (just accept the default values):

 openssl genrsa  -out server.key 1024
 openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr
 cp server.key server.key.org
 openssl rsa -in server.key.org -out server.key
 openssl x509 -req -days 720 -in server.csr -signkey server.key -out server.crt

 start a server process, listening on port 9999:

 openssl s_server -key server.key -cert server.crt -accept 9999

 connect a client to the server:

 openssl s_client -connect localhost:9999

The last command will print out the various compression settings (similar to wireshark), what I see (on Debian 7) is that compression is enabled by default:

 Compression: zlib compression
 Expansion: zlib compression

(I think newer Ubuntu kernels may disable SSL compression by default.)

It would be nice to know if the bleeding edge urllib3 change means that the swift client itself decides not to use compression.'}, {'account_id': 9311, 'date': '2014-02-03 16:13:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Yes that was it, ubuntu have ssl compression disabled by default.

Just tried the requests lib on Debian 7, and ssl compression was enabled (Compression Method: DEFLATE (1)).

I did also tried the urllib3 recent merge (https://github.com/shazow/urllib3/commit/260e1b4f4ee12f46e134ffa59bf56ee956aeabcd)
and the fix is not working for our python2.7 usage. You can see line 610 of urllib3/util.py that this fixes python 3.2+.

We may get lucky with the pyopenssl contibution that requests can use, but it will introduces more dependencies (ie ndg-httpsclient, OpenSSL python module, ...)'}, {'account_id': 9311, 'date': '2014-02-05 19:43:31.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-05 19:54:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

Ok. I can confirm that this patch does turn off SSL compression by default (tested against Requests 2.2.1 on Debian Wheezy). For this to work on python2.7, you will also need to install PyOpenSSL ndg-httpsclient and pyasn1. This should be added to requirements (or wherever the relevant place is for packages only required in python2.7) assuming we're all comfortable with the dependency on openssl.

Following on from that, the CLI option --no-ssl-compression is now a no-op. I think this should probably be marked as deprecated.

This patch also seems to break swift upload when specifying --segment-size. Could someone else confirm this?

Proxy log here: http://paste.openstack.org/show/63893/"}, {'account_id': 866, 'date': '2014-02-10 14:16:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Cut and paste of Samuel Merritt's comment from our previous try at enabling cert checking by default (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/33473/ review of patch set 8).

----------
 If we want to do this, we'll have to bump the version of    swiftclient from 1.x to 2.0 because there are clusters with self-signed, expired, or otherwise bogus certificates out there, and there are client apps using swiftclient 1.x to talk to them, and those apps will break with this change. Breaking change --> major version bump.

That said, I think it's worth doing, but we'll have to trumpet this change from the rooftops to make sure people aren't surprised.
--------"}, {'account_id': 866, 'date': '2014-02-12 10:24:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

Requests 1.1.0 is the oldest stable version having everything we need for swiftclient usage. This is also the stock version of CentOS6, which have been a concern raised by John on the forth comment of this review.

Distributions stepped up for CRIME attacks and patch their ssl libraries to disable compression by default. See comment 31 of https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857051 and https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=728055

Sadly, a default install of Debian 7.4 (without bpo) does not have this patched version of SSL, and thus will compress SSL traffic by default.'}, {'account_id': 866, 'date': '2014-02-12 12:16:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10:

+1 to what tristan said i don't think we can do the work for the distros if they are not providing an update for disabling SSL compression. commit_message:
Port to python-requests

Currently, httplib implementation does not support SSL certificate
verification. This patch fixes this. Note that ssl compression parameter
and 100-continue thing is still missing from requests, though those are
lower priority.

Requests now takes care of:
* proxy configuration (get_environ_proxies),
* chunked encoding (with data generator),
* bulk uploading (with files dictionary),
* SSL certificate verification (with 'insecure' and 'cacert' parameter).

This patch have been tested with requests 1.1.0 (CentOS 6) and requests
2.2.1 (current version).

Change-Id: Ib5de962f4102d57c71ad85fd81a615362ef175dc
Closes-Bug: #1199783
DocImpact
SecurityImpact

commit_message:
Syncing policy engine from oslo-incubator

Syncing policy module - commit a53c4dc
Includes patch 0da5de6 implementing Blueprint policy-constant-check

python update.py --nodeps --base keystone --dest-dir ../keystone/ --modules policy

-----
Adds the ability to check any resource's field against a constant
(literal, or string) in the policy.json file.

For instance, I can ensure that only users with field `enabled` set to
False can be deleted with the following rule:
"identity:delete_user": "False:%(target.user.enabled)s",

Or that only the `Member` role can be granted:
"identity:create_grant": "'Member':%(target.role.name)s",
-----

Change-Id: I054271306f20aac47ce5e9dac594bc1989fee56d
Implements: blueprint policy-constant-check

commit_message:
Remove copyright from empty files

According to policy change in HACKING:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#openstack-licensing
empty files should no longer contain copyright notices.

Change-Id: I65e85baf72cf1a413c4b4c8c478587246d4c319a
Closes-Bug: #1262424

commit_message:
Don't create bin/* files magically

Just use import to make scripts available in bin/ instead of
creating these during setup.py install.

Change-Id: I7318bbb77f6564ed58736887e711e1c497873471

commit_message:
Add cmd2 for cliff

cliff was recently adopted by the Oslo project, so its
requirements now need to be included explicitly in the
global requirements list so they are in the mirror for
jobs when cliff is installed from source.

Change-Id: Ie8f9376dea2102c77a3310fe9adf56074c6fe25f

This change has been discussed and planned for a while. We have not used
migrations much in TripleO, so it was not clear that it was necessary.
But as we move to HA deployments we need a way to run scripts after the
system state has been asserted, which is what migration is for.

Change-Id: I16d90abb3fccc791001beb5d8ed267fcd00f820c
'}]
commit_message:
Move migration to run after post-configure

This change has been discussed and planned for a while. We have not used
migrations much in TripleO, so it was not clear that it was necessary.
But as we move to HA deployments we need a way to run scripts after the
system state has been asserted, which is what migration is for.

Change-Id: I16d90abb3fccc791001beb5d8ed267fcd00f820c

commit_message:
Seed specific Fedora network configuration

When building seed images on Fedora we want to disable
the normal network interface naming conventions and just
go with eth0.

Change-Id: I8551af2d28327a36c5d21007a88057c14b7f9e2e

commit_message:
Add DB mappings with NSX logical routers

This patch introduces DB mappings between neutron and NSX router,
thus not requiring anymore the Neutron router ID to be equal to the
NSX one.

This change is needed for enabling asynchronous operations in
the NSX plugin.

This patch also performs NVP/NSX renaming where appropriate, and
fixes delete router logic causing a 500 HTTP error to be returned
when a Neutron internal error occurs.

Related to blueprint nvp-async-backend-communication
Related to blueprint nicira-plugin-renaming

Change-Id: Ib0e9ed0f58e7fa3497a93e9cd3baa9cb81ad797b

[{'created': '2014-02-11 21:50:39.000000000', 'message': "Update to new hp3parclient

The updated hp3parclient v3.0.0 is required for the new HP 3PAR
cinder driver and it's unit tests.  This patch is the first in
2 patches that are need to land.  We are breaking this up into
2 patches to avoid breaking continuous deployment.

First we'll update the top end to 4.0 in this patch.  The
next patch will update the low end to 3.0.

Change-Id: I2d0f92b7d082637d55f4bbc7cac66c97aa73cfe0
"}]
commit_message:
Update to new hp3parclient

The updated hp3parclient v3.0.0 is required for the new HP 3PAR
cinder driver and it's unit tests.  This patch is the first in
2 patches that are need to land.  We are breaking this up into
2 patches to avoid breaking continuous deployment.

First we'll update the top end to 4.0 in this patch.  The
next patch will update the low end to 3.0.

Change-Id: I2d0f92b7d082637d55f4bbc7cac66c97aa73cfe0

commit_message:
Add a note about python2.6 support to the README

This commit adds a new section to the tempest README regarding python2.6
with tempest. It also outlines the steps required to enable testr with
python2.6.

commit_message:
Some small async utils tweaks

- Renames waiter to any waiter (since its event will be triggered
  on any result/exception/cancellation).
- Import _base and use that instead of going through futures._base.
- Use a static set of finished states instead of creating a new
  list everytime the _done_futures function is called.

Change-Id: I3ca8057ea8047359bf99a6acb00b3b6fd4d75f92

commit_message:
Inject rather than read-out the virt power key.

Currently we make a throwaway key when using the virtual power
manager. This doesn't work all that well - users authorised_key files
get huge - and it doesn't work at all for Tripleo-CI.

Change-Id: I93191f8716a9e77da789a12c531ffa00bcd6cd5b

commit_message:
Replace nonexistent mock assert methods with real ones

Methods like assert_not_called, assert_called_once, assert_called do
not exist, they generated on the fly (dummy) and don't assert anything.
This patch replaces each of nonexistent method calls with real.

Change-Id: I12ac093b81a7a90b9b3771678ea2cc3c2a40c876
Closes-Bug: #1272428

commit_message:
Log IPMI power on/off timeouts

Ported from nova: Iecd6fadb2b653f4ccbe75882c2ef85812b334e8d

Added log messages for cloud operators so that they can tell when an
attempt to turn a device on or off via IPMI has failed after the
configured number of attempts.

This should help operators diagnose issues on devices that respond
slowly to IPMI commands. The failure to repeatedly change the device
power state is now logged precisely along with the cause, where
before operators had to diagnose the issue through trace log captures.

Change-Id: I06cd432c72d72f5abe8cd5941e4d5844c66c1482

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-16 13:23:38.000000000', 'message': 'Add support for user/admin roles to the deploy object

Instead of storing the endpoints as a simple admin credentials dictionary
(containing the username, password etc.) the deploy object should store
more information, i.e. whether the deployment is going to be used with
the predefined set of users (the "user" role) or the users should be
generated (the "admin" role) and what are the actual credentials of these
users. This information now gets stored in a dictionary of form:

"endpoints" : {
    "role": "admin|user",
    "credentials": [
        {"username": ..., "password": ..., "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ...},
        {"username": ..., "password": ..., "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ...},
        ...
    ]
}

Blueprint benchmarking-with-predefined-users

Change-Id: If36e33e89daa036bd4b0d7db8e2d3b5b5b0f4aca

commit_message:
Add support for user/admin permissions in endpoints

Instead of storing the endpoints as a single admin credentials dictionary
(containing the username, password etc.) we should be able to store several
endpoints which can be possibly returned from the deploy object, as well as
the information whether these endpoints have the admin permission or not.
If not, then the deployment is going to be used with the predefined set of
users (that will be implemented next). If there is an admin endpoint, then
the users for benchmarking will be generated (the "admin" role).
This information now gets stored in a dictionary of form:

    "endpoints": [
        {"username": ..., "password": ...,
         "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ..., "permission": "admin|user"},
        {"username": ..., "password": ...,
         "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ...,
         "permission": "admin|user"},
        ...
    ]

Blueprint benchmarking-with-predefined-users

Change-Id: If36e33e89daa036bd4b0d7db8e2d3b5b5b0f4aca

commit_message:
Remove s3_token functional tests

The s3_token middleware was moved to keystoneclient but the tests
were left to ensure backwards compatibility. The tests have passed
since then and the keystoneclient of the s3_token middleware has
already diverged that causes the tests to fail.

The functional tests are removed and replaced with a test to
ensure that the symbols are forwarded properly.

bp s3-token-to-keystoneclient

Change-Id: Ie1cea741d33400eaa4d4afc7206a3ba1db9a4573

commit_message:
Support TripleO-CI for overcloud builds.

For Tripleo-CI we can't generate the key in the VM and hand it out,
because we have restricted access to the machine. Plus, this has been
ugly forever. Pass an SSH key in, rather than pulling one out.

Change-Id: I1def0757758e30e63891ff099106dac158bd8d83

commit_message:
Allow manual hosts entry exports in overcloud.

This makes it possible to have SSL connections to APIs from compute
hosts with no DNS or external connectivity - something the
ci-overcloud has.

Change-Id: I089ef8fdfb4a59279f09bf3cd2a4474000e4bfa6

commit_message:
Fixup missing variables for CI.

For CI we had a number of (tightly related) missing variables:
 - The SSH key has to be passed in, not generated in-instance
 - The host is not 192.168.122.1
 - The arch etc all come from the test environment the test is
   running on so we need to read them from the JSON.

Change-Id: Ia373cd2007750a2ce5ad0b1ee18cf3c44591d9dc
Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>

commit_message:
Allow setting of publish directory

You can now set the publication directory for a book. This will
allow to make more generic Jenkins jobs since we can now say for example
that api-quick-start-onepager-external gets published as
api-quick-start.

Fix publishing so that books published to trunk or havana etc are
copied to the proper subdirectory of publish-docs.

Change-Id: Ifb45a352e6f803321dcfcfcc5f8f17b7876f209b

commit_message:
Stop catting tempest.config during tempest setup

This commit removes the 'cat tempest.config' from lib/tempest. There
is no reason to cat it as part of running devstack because the file
is and can be interacted with after devstack finishes running. To
prevent a loss of information in the gate this change should be
coupled with devstack-gate change: Ifb36918cd0d686cb3865f5322cd62c209acaaf30
which copies the tempest.config file with the other test artifacts.

Change-Id: Ia01cd53660b3490ea9faa9e9c746bafd9df12a9b

Don't warn about heat modifying flavors

Since de0898a Heat no longer modifies flavors, so the comment
and output related to modified flavors is no longer needed.

Change-Id: I1007d2ab3387f28b8d7487f450cab4592f2824aa

commit_message:
Move every rally command to its own module

Move all the currently supported rally commands (i.e. deployment, task,
use) and their equivalent tests that are described as classes in
the 'main.py' module (and 'test_main.py' module), to separate modules in
a new directory. This is done for organizing the code of the rally command
line utility, before it become too big.

Implements: blueprint rally-show-command
Change-Id: I5982f854dfe64604ae112d93fb7ea68f72657b98

Rename Queue related methods for VMware NSX plugin

This is the first step of many for renaming/refactoring
nvplib and related modules. Starting with queues, whose
code is small and less daunting.

Partial-implements blueprint: nicira-plugin-renaming

Change-Id: I2db899883c61f30c8b15703c96290872e853d670

Fix service name for marconi

marconi service.

subject: Lets not recommend stackuser is used on testenv images
messages:
[{'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-07 17:19:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-07 17:23:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Works for me

Build succeeded.

- gate-noop http://logs.openstack.org/54/71954/1/check/gate-noop/6456bd9 : SUCCESS in 0s
'}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2014-02-07 17:30:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

If network connectivity gets hosed... then how would we debug these on the console?

Given we don't allows passwords for SSH connections this seems reasonable to have in our image list right?"}, {'account_id': 1926, 'date': '2014-02-07 17:48:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Ya you could be right, its reasonable that people would want to log in over remote terminal or something but a password hardcoded to stack probably isn't what they would want."}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2014-02-07 17:51:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Derek: so what if we added an option so that the stackuser password was a parameter. Leave the default as is... but you could optionally supply a better password that wouldn't be known to the world."}, {'account_id': 1926, 'date': '2014-02-07 18:10:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

would work for me.'}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2014-02-07 18:54:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

testenv machines are entirely attackable by tripleo-gate, so +1 on not recommending it, OTOH we do need something.

That said, this shouldn't be static per machine, rather random and recorded by heat so we can get at it if needed."}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2014-02-07 19:24:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer); Approved

Since this is only a comment I'm fine w/ it. Good luck to whomever builds an image with no console access though."}, {'account_id': 1926, 'date': '2014-02-13 16:33:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Remove _load_one_plugin fallback

Remove the _load_one_plugin fallback for stevedore version < 0.14. The
commit c011d7360085dc5b2b2521e5c533ccc87b310f15 pinned the stevedore
version to >= 0.14.

Change-Id: I73ab108a55613d9b9f6ce577d7a90ffe6596bd2c

commit_message:
Remove POST calls in tests for resource creation

Removes all unnecessary POST calls in tests setup.  Any resources needed in
test setup are now created with a direct call to the DB API.

Change-Id: I2b19eeb25e563a658eaf375c8ae83dec9ff68deb
Closes-Bug: #1261398

[{'created': '2014-02-08 08:27:55.000000000', 'message': 'Add samples to serve API through Apache mod_wsgi

The default API service (ironic.cmd.api) uses the wsgiref library,
and is single-threaded. Deployers are likely to want to serve the API
from a more robust web server such as Apache2.

This patch adds application hooks to use with mod_wsgi,
and a sample apache2 config file to demonstrate its use.

Change-Id: I44cd8e0941c350a6e5c16cf2d068c3e8d684ab47
'}, {'created': '2014-02-12 06:53:07.000000000', 'message': 'Add samples to serve API through Apache mod_wsgi

The default API service (ironic.cmd.api) uses the wsgiref library.

Some deployers may want to serve the API through apache/httpd instead.

This patch adds application hooks to use with mod_wsgi, and a sample
apache2 config file to demonstrate its use with debian-based distros.

Change-Id: I44cd8e0941c350a6e5c16cf2d068c3e8d684ab47
Related-bug: #1279206
'}]
commit_message:
Add samples to serve API through Apache mod_wsgi

The default API service (ironic.cmd.api) uses the wsgiref library.

Some deployers may want to serve the API through apache/httpd instead.

This patch adds application hooks to use with mod_wsgi, and a sample
apache2 config file to demonstrate its use with debian-based distros.

Change-Id: I44cd8e0941c350a6e5c16cf2d068c3e8d684ab47
Related-bug: #1279206

commit_message:
Fixture to reraise exceptions raised during logging

Add fixture to monkey patch logging.Handler.handleError to raise
exceptions generated when trying to emit a log.

Implements blueprint logging-handleerror-raise-exception

Change-Id: I7a4ab4f181634ed5b92ce88e9ed1d976ecb633a7

[{'created': '2014-02-13 06:52:19.000000000', 'message': 'Node power state is not printed after set

As of commit 4676d823a8a35 to Ironic, the API for changing Node power
state no longer returns a body. With no return body, there is nothing
to print in the CLI after requesting the power state change.

This patch removes the print-out of an empty table when the CLI
set-node-power-state command is issued.

Change-Id: If1fb035bdf83e36e3a6a13e639efadc370c40887
Related-bug: #1270160
'}]
commit_message:
Node power state is not printed after set

As of commit 4676d823a8a35 to Ironic, the API for changing Node power
state no longer returns a body. With no return body, there is nothing
to print in the CLI after requesting the power state change.

This patch removes the print-out of an empty table when the CLI
set-node-power-state command is issued.

Change-Id: If1fb035bdf83e36e3a6a13e639efadc370c40887

commit_message:
Return node_uuid from a port-show cmd

A port-show command returned these fields: address, created_at, extra,
updated_at, and uuid. The node_uuid associated with the port is also
returned with this change.

Change-Id: If345406d5a00bed7e5acfaa6e710f3cdb39b07ac
Closes-Bug: #1279552

commit_message:
Add topic to the change_node_maintenance_mode() RPC method

Topic is used by the distributed hashing algorithm in order to know to
which conductor it should route the RPC messages to. All the methods in
the rpcapi should support passing a topic to it.

Change-Id: Ida9f2efd07cf5a4f1445f68cdc8aac4e752a8c7a

commit_message:
raise SystemExit instead of calling exit()

exit is a constant meant to be used in the interpreter, not in code:

    >>> print(exit)
    Use exit() or Ctrl-D (i.e. EOF) to exit
    >>> exit()

Change-Id: I35825c81fb33eb7ab6b8bd7279110b2ee3271ea3

I have two concerns about this implementation:

[{'created': '2014-01-25 16:30:45.000000000', 'message': "Fix race condition when changing node states

To fix race condition we're adding a mechanism of background task
execution in conductor. The conductor will get synchrozed AMQP call,
reserve lock and validate task parameters, start the task in a background
and return empty response to AMQP producer. In case when lock cannot
be acquired or parameters are invalid the exception is sent back to
the AMQP producer and the task is not started.

Also the patch adds an ability to control resource locks manually.
This feauture used to release lock in the end of background task.

commit_message:
Fix race condition when changing node states

To fix race condition we're adding a mechanism of background task
execution in conductor. The conductor will get synchrozed AMQP call,
reserve lock, start the background task and return empty response to
the API. In case when lock cannot be acquired or background tasks pool
is full, the exception is sent back to the API and the task is not
started.

Also the patch adds an ability to control resource locks manually.
This feauture used to release lock in the end of background task.

Change-Id: I4095de2d82058ea5e052531698e67a0947424435
Closes-Bug: #1259910

commit_message:
Make 'virtual_size' read-only for v1

If a server has both v2 and v1 enabled a user should not be able
to use the v1 api to change 'virtual_size'.

Change-Id: I034e8d6bd3fdbda34f3d833f8087a6a1b8dfdde4

commit_message:
Don't allow compute_node free_disk_gb to be None

As part of commit 5668870, we now explicitly guard against the case
free_disk_gb is None or unset. However, this should never happen
since resource tracker always sets it and guarding against this case
isn't actually needed to fix the bug in question.

Also, simplify the code a little to make the intent more clear. We
assume that free_disk_gb is always set, but we want to use
disk_available_least where the driver has set it. The case where
disk_available_least is less than free_disk_gb is the exceptional
case we want to guard against.

Change-Id: I3973eab6b4ca016df546de8b57245fc0d0f03a80

Add test_set dependency to models

Fields "master_testset" and "slave_testset" were added to TestSet entity
in models.py. This data defines test sets hierarchy for building test
runs execution chains. New migration version was generated for new data
scheme. Fixture tests were updated with purpose to support new logic

commit_message:
Add Fedora DHCP interfaces via udev rules

Updates the dhcp-all-interfaces element so that
we add new DHCP interfaces using a udev rule
instead of a systemd service.

The previous approach (using the systemd service)
was proving to be problematic when used with
the new Fedora constistent network naming
convention rules (em1, em2, etc.). We aren't using
these device names as a default yet... but we will
need to soon and when we do udev rules seem to be the
best way to avoid racy behaviour when calling
dhcp-all-interfaces.sh from the systemd service.

Change-Id: I87e0aed1f34718e896bd414388886a1f1073b0c0

commit_message:
Support adding DHCP interfaces one at a time.

Refactors dhcp-all-interfaces.sh so that if an optional
INTERFACE argument (the first argument) is passed to the script
it only inspects that single interface. If no argument is
passed then the previous default behaviour use used which
causes all interfaces to be inspected.

Also sets PATH so that the commands within the script
can all be found if it isn't set properly (/sbin/ip, /bin/cat, etc.)

This is a move towards using udev rules to add these types
of interfaces automatically.

Change-Id: Ia482c1d3ddce0f0d8d77f9bc3ac76d6924640715

[{'created': '2014-02-11 17:08:36.000000000', 'message': 'Propogate cacert and insecure flags to glanceclient

Fixes bug 1278973

Previously, the insecure flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient
while the cacert flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient and
the ceilometerclient used by alarming.

Since the glanceclient also supports these options, these flags should
be propogated to it also to avoid SSL cert verification failures when the

Change-Id: I967ba080a4011a54b5789ca0fc20cb9a37dafb15
'}]
commit_message:
Propogate cacert and insecure flags to glanceclient

Fixes bug 1278973

Previously, the insecure flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient
while the cacert flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient and
the ceilometerclient used by alarming.

Since the glanceclient also supports these options, these flags should
be propogated to it also to avoid SSL cert verification failures when the
central agent calls out to glance over https.

Change-Id: I967ba080a4011a54b5789ca0fc20cb9a37dafb15

machines, so we no longer have to ship the configuration change in our
nova.conf.

Change-Id: Ieeb890aeb1fb7593e11232b95da40dfadae7962a
'}]
commit_message:
Remove file injection settings from nova.conf

Nova upstream now disables file injection for both baremetal and virtual
machines, so we no longer have to ship the configuration change in our
nova.conf.

Change-Id: Ieeb890aeb1fb7593e11232b95da40dfadae7962a

commit_message:
Don't use cfg.CONF in oslo.db

Using of a global config object is something we want to avoid when
making libraries. Parameters must be passed as function/class methods
arguments instead.

In order not to duplicate options declaration in each project, they
have been put into separate options module (which should not be a
part of oslo.db when it's released; we'll probably want to find a
place for it within oslo-incubator).

Partial-Bug: #1263908

Co-authored-by: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ib5a4e31b4e78e2b4cb807a8c88b8072f4207eb22

commit_message:
Add get_console() method

Add the get_console() method to the base console interface class. When
implemented this method should return the necessary information for the
client to access that console.

Change-Id: Idb1796000b0b7b5a9967fcb756c0b7de5d38f801
Implements: blueprint serial-console-access

[{'created': '2014-01-23 16:26:29.000000000', 'message': "Don't store engine instances in oslo.db

oslo.db is meant to be a collection of helper utilities for
SQLAlchemy. In order to behave like a 'good' library, we must
stop using global state.

This patch ensures we don't store any engine instances globally in
oslo.db. It's up to end applications to decide how to cope with
engines, not oslo.db.

Partial-Bug: #1263908

Change-Id: I330467ec1317e1a13ff9f0237e2d8900d718e379

commit_message:
Don't store engine instances in oslo.db

oslo.db is meant to be a collection of helper utilities for
SQLAlchemy. In order to behave like a 'good' library, we must
stop using global state.

This patch ensures we don't store any engine instances globally in
oslo.db. It's up to end applications to decide how to cope with
engines, not oslo.db.

Partial-Bug: #1263908

Co-authored-by: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I330467ec1317e1a13ff9f0237e2d8900d718e379

commit_message:
Implement _update_neutron in PXE driver

Implement the _update_neutron method in the PXE driver,
so that it may update the DHCP BOOT options in Neutron,
and add unit tests.

Change-Id: I221ac15d9e43e1c8728aa2b100bc02763a160b85
Implements: blueprint add-neutron-support

commit_message:
For mysql with syslog, make local logs copy and provide rotation

For syslog mode, save a local copy of *all* mysql logs to /var/log/mysqld.log
and add it ro retation plans as well.
(Does not change remote logging headers)

Closes bug: #1275124

Change-Id: I322594fdf47329e914526168eda42f9dd16a3201
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Add needed swift storage dirs for packaged install

These directories are needed by both the packaged and source installs,
so do their creation into a common install.d script instead.

Change-Id: I7a05030015d17cf33f7fa231a199d78dc9e86b0b

commit_message:
Add `virtual_size` to Glance's API v2

This patch adds the knowledge of a virtual_size field to Glance's API
v2. The virtual_size field should respect the same rules applied to the
size field in terms of readability, access control and propagation.

Glance's API v1 has been left unmodified.

docImpact
Implements blueprint: split-image-size

Change-Id: Ie4f58ee2e4da3a6c1229840295c7f62023a95b70

subject: Add a virtual_size attribute to the Image model

commit_message:
Add a virtual_size attribute to the Image model

In order to distinguish file size from the virtual image size, we need
to add a new field to the Image model to represent that. This patch adds
a new field called `virtual_size` to the Image model and the migration
for it.

The existing size attribute is kept as is in order to keep backwards
compatibility. Most of the users consider that attribute to be the
physical image size, which is what we're trying to achieve here.

The API implementation will be done in a follow-up patch.

Partially-Implements bp: split-image-size

Change-Id: Ie968e8bcfaeda79de003fe8fd7a3b58c3e45f592

commit_message:
create the key to be used by the virt power driver

this is the key that comes from the TE host, the nova baremetal nodes
need it so that they can ssh to TE host and control virsh. The
tripleo-incubator scripts pick it up from ~/.ssh/id_rsa_virt_power.

Change-Id: I70406a3e79af1e66d85117588a144b3ec677909b

commit_message:
Extension absence handling

Handling the case of extension absence or wrong extension name. The case
never been handled directly, but this became obvious only after
`find_migrate_repo` usage was fixed.

Change-Id: I64ea2e9bf71bd470a053a7ab6d5acf7e9776d997

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:

commit_message:
Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

Closes bug: #1275838

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

manually merged from heat master commit:
472c1440677440e0888570926b49542ddf260724

which is, in turn, from upstream oslo-incubator commit:
b4f72b2987d53bb434e3a833f06d70a2167f5efc

Change-Id: I0a00bf23f575fb0795a84eca5a35560d4fe7ec53

commit_message:
Correct error class in find_migrate_repo

AssertionError mustn't be used in production code. This complicates error
handling.

Change-Id: I353a2c4cd9b8bb97fffb59918f00dbbf2f326f91

(2 inline comments)

Hi Brianna, could you explain a little why updating an encryption that associated with a in-use type is not permitted in this extension. For similar cases like updating the specs for instance flavors or volume types, Nova/Cinder doesn't stop user from doing that even if flavors/types are in-use. So my first thought is we should allow user updating in-use encryption and leave those existing volumes alone.  Otherwise, it's possible that once encryption is used, it can hardly be changed in real deployment, because volumes were created using the type.  But I may be wrong in this case, so I'd like to understand more about this restriction.  Thanks."}, {'account_id': 7012, 'date': '2013-12-05 23:38:24.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 7012, 'date': '2013-12-05 23:43:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: (3 inline comments)

'}, {'account_id': 7012, 'date': '2013-12-05 23:55:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hello Huang,

The reason that updating an encrypted volume type while there are volumes in use is a problem is because this has the potential to render encrypted volumes inaccessible due to the changes.  Even if the volumes were to remain accessible (by having the needed metadata stored locally with the volume) it would still be confusing for the administrator because the parameters in the volume type and the parameters in a volume of that volume type could be different.  The administrator may think that all volumes of the type have a certain key size, but in reality some volumes have one, and some another.

I think it is still valuable to provide basic update support even if it is limited, with the idea that it could be improved at a later point.  A more complex solution may be to do a complete un-encrypting and re-encrypting of all of the volumes in use with the new parameters, which would remove the restriction and keep uniformity for the volumes of the volume type.

A use case for the simple update support: If one were to create the encryption, and then realize that the key size entered was wrong immediately after, it would be useful to have a method to quickly modify the key size and update the encryption (which would happen before any volumes had been created with that volume type).  

Also, if all of the volumes that were using the volume type have been deleted, then updating encryption would be permitted.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-06 00:15:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Works for me

commit_message:
Add update support to volume type encryption

This patch adds update support to the Volume Type Encryption API
Extension.  It allows the updating of volume type encryption for
a given volume type as long as no volumes are currently in use
with that volume type.

Change-Id: If5f9ef792626e7dfaf82365bb6838b964f8238ae
Implements: blueprint encrypt-cinder-volumes
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/encrypt-cinder-volumes

commit_message:
Adds a fixture for setting up the cache

Certain tests will fail in isolation becasue the cache isn't properly
configured. This fixture will clear out any old configuration and
correctly configure the cache.

Change-Id: I6ec944880dea930771906a63a76400fe3d10e299
Closes-Bug: #1251300

commit_message:
nec plugin: Compare OFS datapath_id as hex int

Previously NEC plugin compares old and new datapath_ids as
a string and zero padding in hex notation is not taken into
account when compared. This causes unintended deletion and
recreation of a port on OpenFlow controller. This patch fixes
this issue by comparing datapath_ids as hex int.

Change-Id: I6aa0a041e98c9bc489af89bb642ec5f86eaecce5
Closes-Bug: 1278349

commit_message:
Retrieve user_id from HTTP Headers to populate Context

We need the user_id within notifications sent by Heat to be able to
handle it in Ceilometer, currently only the username is provided which
can be non-uniq per tenant and could confuse the integrity of data.
The easiest way to do that is to populate the Context within the user_id
retrieved from Headers.
No need to store the user_id in Heat backend.

Related-Blueprint: send-notification

Change-Id: I88bd5612556d2000d72427308d17643f14d35306

commit_message:
Implement HOT intrinsic function get_file

This function takes a single string argument and uses that as the key
in a lookup into the template files. The resulting content is substituted
as a chunk of text.

The files keys can be arbitrary and the files section can be built manually
when generating the API request. However by convention heatclient will use
the absolute URL of the file as the key.

Change-Id: I83a73b14e1fbf56545151da1d8a0d7afe89149a4

commit_message:
Switch to the default cloud-init user

This removes `setenforce 0` from boothook.sh, creating a custom user
and adding them to sudoers in favour of just defaulting to the user
that comes with cloud-init for each specific distro.

The downside is that we no longer have the same cross-distro username
(ec2-user by default), instead it's whatever the distro ships
("fedora" on Fedora 19+, "ubuntu" on Ubuntu 12.04+ and "cloud-user" on
CentOS/RHEL). However, it's easy to add a new user via a Heat
template.

The upside is that SELinux is set up correctly without us having to do
anything (specifically no 0.6.9 vs. 0.7.2 cloud-init version
incompatibilities) and we ship less code while being more robust.

Tested on Fedora 20, Ubuntu 12.04 LTS, Ubuntu 13.10, CentOS 6.5 and
RHEL 6.5 cloud images.

Change-Id: I6710b4563b9e26c8b0451ee2019f7606c7dbf098
Closes-Bug: #1257410

Add a nova keypair constraint

The patch adds a new custom constraint validating nova keypairs, and
uses it in the Instance and Server resources.

blueprint param-constraints
Co-Authored-By: cedric.soulas@cloudwatt.com

commit_message:
Avoid using assertGreater

assertGreater doesn't exist in python 2.6.
The commit 32173d1cc5b5300c04ffd4da988827354bd07fa3 changes the ones of
Nova v2 API tests, and this patch covers v3 API tests.

Change-Id: Ib283aa8d70aa093eff03fa5d6ec477ea9766c727

commit_message:
Adding status field to image location -- DB migration

Adding a status field to image's each location property, each location
status can be 'active', 'pending_delete' and 'deleted'.

Under location's status information Scrubber service can make cleanup
based on DB records also but not a dedicated queue-file for each image.

This is first part of this change which covered DB core migration.

Partially-Implements BP: image-location-status

Change-Id: I013b70d55ef14a3ceaca962f9bc48296cb8b2552
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Improve help strings

Follow oslo.config style guide for help strings better to create
consistent help strings:
* Capitalize first word of each help string
* Finish help strings with "."
* Improve wording
* Add missing space between strings

Change-Id: Ia86734d44fdf4eb3711fef800fe6bdfd1a1b59d4

commit_message:
Correct host managers free disk calculation

Take lower of disk_least_available/free_disk_gb if they exist.

When an instance exists in the database but not on the hypervisor
(which can happen in some error cases), the 'missing' instance
is included in the calculation of 'free_gb' but not included in
'disk_available_least'.
Need to take the value that represents the minimum amount of free
disk space available.

Testing:
COMPUTE_NODES in fakes.py includes the 4 possible test cases:
    disk_least_available or free_disk_gb = free_disk_mb
        None             or     512      =    524288
        1024             or    None      =   1048576
        3333             or    3072      =   3145728
        8192             or    8888      =   8388608
   test: test_host_manager.py
           test_get_all_host_states:
             Already has existing tests looking for these
             cases - I've modifed the test data (in fakes.py)
             rather than creating new test data.
             Added check for Warning message for node 3 where
             physical disk (3333) is greater than database (3072)
         No impact on other tests.

Change-Id: I4a18bf023a64d0cb198f77aab9daecb0786e93ff
Closes-Bug: 1253599

commit_message:
Add attribute for image api workers setting

- Add an attribute for ['openstack']['image']['api']['workers']
- Adjust the template for glance-api.conf to use this attributes
- Adjust the default value to be a maximum of 8 (but this can be
  overridden)
- Adjust spec tests to set the cpu value so they converge
- Add test to confirm this value can be set
- Add test to confirm the .min[8 , sets a max of 8.
- Add README.md attribute entry

Change-Id: I8bdbd8bc8fe9af7a9ca3bbc8856d5a200ce7be7b
Closes-Bug: #1274884

commit_message:
Storage protects lower level backend against thread safety

The storage changes to use a read/write lock provide locking
guarantees that we do not need to duplicate in the underlying
storage.

This is predicated on the fact that we do the following:

1. A user before running upgrades the schema of there backend
   before giving the logbook/backend to the engine. This means
   that the backend upgrade() method does not need to be
   thread safe.
2. One engine working on one logbook at a given time.
3. An engine accesses and uses the logbook and its flow/task
   details by accessing data via the storage accessor interface.
4. Tasks do not currently get direct access to storage or the
   underlying logbook while running (in the future we could
   provide access to a storage object, but we would need to have
   a contract that ensures a task can not hijack an engines usage
   of storage by deadlocking the engine).

Change-Id: I0efd5333928698802d25e1ff124e781f9a4907d9

commit_message:
Delete raise skip if AssertionError was happens

Proboscis do not skip tests if parent was skipped
so to skip tests that depends on parent try except
block with raise SkipTest() was removed

Change-Id: Ia886292b9ebca81bb74cc7bba1e88d3322e1cb4a

commit_message:
Script for exporting jenkins test report to Google spreadsheet

Example: python report-exporter -j my-job-name -s 0AhZjx9R84sqXdGFSdnNhUGhDQlNGN6dMamZMSVlZdFE
following environment variables should be specified before launching
JENKINS_HOME - jenkins home page URL
GOOGLE_LOGIN, GOOGLE_PASSWORD - google account credentials

It exports test report of the last run of a specified job to
google spreadsheet document. A sheet name will be named <job-name>.
Sheet format example:
name        build1    build2    build3   ...
testname1   pass      fail      fail
testname2   pass      pass      fail
...

Change-Id: Ie90bba9c34f282336bfd957aa37d1af184dfb7d5

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-09 01:46:51.000000000', 'message': 'Finish configuring a service before adding it to HAProxy

Starting an HAProxy instance for ceilometer-api (and possibly other
similar services) will fail on Ubuntu if the package for that service is
installed but not yet configured: the service is still running in its
default configuration binding to 0.0.0.0 instead of just the management
IP, preventing HAProxy from binding to the management VIP on the same
port.

To prevent a dependency loop (Ceilometer, like most other OpenStack
services, depends on MySQL), Galera dependencies have to be narrowed
down from the whole of HAProxy setup to just the registration of MySQL
service with it. HAProxy related parts of controller_ha and galera
classes are refactored to support reloading HAProxy for each service
independently, and to group together HAProxy options specific to
individual services.

Added "--no-class_inherits_from_params_class-check" to puppet-lint
options to prevent it from issuing a warning that is not relevant for
Puppet versions 2.7 and newer.

Change-Id: I5fa03dbc3f7e3a7dfa57c226a5396f652c111997
Closes-bug: #1264388

'}, {'created': '2014-01-29 00:54:37.000000000', 'message': 'Finish configuring a service before adding it to HAProxy

Starting an HAProxy instance for ceilometer-api (and possibly other
similar services) will fail on Ubuntu if the package for that service is
installed but not yet configured: the service is still running in its
default configuration binding to 0.0.0.0 instead of just the management
IP, preventing HAProxy from binding to the management VIP on the same
port.

To prevent a dependency loop (Ceilometer, like most other OpenStack
services, depends on MySQL), Galera dependencies have to be narrowed
down from the whole of HAProxy setup to just the registration of MySQL
service with it. HAProxy related parts of controller_ha and galera
classes are refactored to support reloading HAProxy for each service
independently, and to group together HAProxy options specific to
individual services.

To support granular addition of services into HAProxy, haproxy module
updated to puppetlabs-haproxy 1.0.1 (0d4c50e) and refactored to split
haproxy.cfg into multiple files under /etc/haproxy/conf.d using include
directive as implemented in the patch by Brane F. Gračnar:

http://marc.info/?l=haproxy&m=129235503410444

The define_backends option for haproxy class introduced in Fuel is
renamed to define_backups and ported to the new haproxy module.

Support for selecting exported haproxy::balancermember resources by tag
is dropped since it is no longer used (and not relevant since Fuel no
longer runs puppetmaster).

An ordered list of controllers is passed from osnailyfacter::cluster_ha
to openstack::controller_ha so that haproxy::balancermember always sets
the primary controller as the active server in failover configurations.

HAProxy configuration for RadosGW is changed from active-passive
failover to active-active load balancing between controller nodes.
Backend IP addresses for RadosGW servers are changed from storage to
internal.

Added "--no-class_inherits_from_params_class-check" to puppet-lint
options to prevent it from issuing a warning that is not relevant for
Puppet versions 2.7 and newer.

Change-Id: I5fa03dbc3f7e3a7dfa57c226a5396f652c111997
Closes-bug: #1264388

Starting an HAProxy instance for ceilometer-api (and possibly other
similar services) will fail on Ubuntu if the package for that service is
installed but not yet configured: the service is still running in its
default configuration binding to 0.0.0.0 instead of just the management
IP, preventing HAProxy from binding to the management VIP on the same
port.

To prevent a dependency loop (Ceilometer, like most other OpenStack
services, depends on MySQL), Galera dependencies have to be narrowed
down from the whole of HAProxy setup to just the registration of MySQL
service with it. HAProxy related parts of controller_ha and galera
classes are refactored to support reloading HAProxy for each service
independently, and to group together HAProxy options specific to
individual services.

To support granular addition of services into HAProxy, haproxy module
updated to puppetlabs-haproxy 1.0.1 (0d4c50e) and refactored to split
haproxy.cfg into multiple files under /etc/haproxy/conf.d using include
directive as implemented in the patch by Brane F. Gračnar:

http://marc.info/?l=haproxy&m=129235503410444

The define_backends option for haproxy class introduced in Fuel is
renamed to define_backups and ported to the new haproxy module.

Support for selecting exported haproxy::balancermember resources by tag
is dropped since it is no longer used (and not relevant since Fuel no
longer runs puppetmaster).

An ordered list of controllers is passed from osnailyfacter::cluster_ha
to openstack::controller_ha so that haproxy::balancermember always sets
the primary controller as the active server in failover configurations.

HAProxy is now configured as part the "main" stage, so "cluster_head"
stage is no longer necessary. MySQL and RabbitMQ listen blocks are
populated before HAProxy is first started, other listen blocks are added
incrementally with HAProxy being reloaded via OCF. In HA mode, all
dbsync invokations now require HAProxy MySQL (Ceilometer and Heat were
missing), and all OpenStack services now require HAProxy Keystone.

HAProxy configuration for RadosGW is changed from active-passive
failover to active-active load balancing between controller nodes.
Backend IP addresses for RadosGW servers are changed from storage to
internal.

HAProxy mode option handling is cleaned up so that the default "http"
mode now propagates properly for listening services that do not specify
"tcp" mode explicitly.

Syslog facility for Ceilometer changed from SYSLOG to LOG_SYSLOG to
catch up to the cleanup done in LP #1263675.

Added "--no-class_inherits_from_params_class-check" to puppet-lint
options to prevent it from issuing a warning that is not relevant for
